author: CY Kang
text:
Experienced an unpleasant moment. One of your staff approached me claiming that I called my friend "FAT" at the entrance which indirectly displays to the visitors that the gym has a bad environment that allows the members to address others as FAT. I truly appreciate his professionalism in his work and effort in forbidding body shaming culture in the gym, however, I had explained to the staff that the word coming out of my mouth was "FEB" (abbreviation for February) as my friend and I were discussing when were we signed up for the gym, he mentioned it was in MARCH or APRIL and I replied to him "FEB" at the entrance. Unfortunately, your staff felt I was being sarcastic and claimed that I was insulting his intelligence. Even though, he said he was not accusing me of anything and just wanted to clarify that the gym doesn't encourage such culture calling others FAT in the gym I had made my stand very clear that I didn't speak any word of FAT and I don't appreciate the way he keep repeating this to me which I had already explained over and over again. Most importantly, the staff is not apologetic at all about his accusations and put a sour face throughout our conversation.

I had paid good money for the use of the club, what I get is this shoddy treatment from your staff.

Further to this, I had emailed on Jan to enquiry on the cancellation after the minimum term. Gotten reply from the assistant manager stated to approach them after my minimum term instead of reminding that there are 30 days of notice period. Luckily this incident happened and I decided to cancel immediately after the min term and it only extend extra two days.

Gym is small with limited equipment, and there are group of customers would hog the equipment for hours, filming video of their lifts and others wouldn't have the chance to share the equipment. There is no control from the staff.

All in all, please avoid this branch and wouldn't recommend this club to others.
source_file: Anytime Fitness Choa Chu Kang Centre_reviews.csv

author: Lee Marcus
text:
Comparing to other Anytime Fitness I have been this gym meets all required facilities with some slight issues due to limited space or poor "tetris-ing".

However, there are some flaws that stood out after visiting other branches.
Gym Equipment:
1) Only 2-3 free Bench can be places at free weights area. (Probably an issue during peak hours only)
2) Only 2 Rope Attachment with 1 Cable machine and another tricep cable machine

Improved to 3.5 stars. Gym Owner is kind enough to ask for feedback and have been rectifying issues urgently. There is urgency to improve the gym for its users. Please be patient and give this gym a chance!

*IMPROVEMENTS
1) Aircon is now on 24/7
2) Theres Music now even in the weee mornings
3) Trash are cleared on a regular basis (Added Signage as well) *See Picture
4) Planning to improve/add some machines and organization of equipments.

Please do note that these issues I have noticed are compared to other gyms I have been at the west side. If time is of the essense, this gym will probably suffice during off peak hours.

author: Jia Hui Lim
text:
This gym has been nothing short of amazing!
When you enter the gym, you'll be greeted by polite and amicable staff.
Plenty of cardio and strength training equipment available, including an open area for you to do warm-ups or your own exercises. Classes are conducted at the open area.
I love how they have equipment not commonly found in other outlets, such as Glute Coaster, Total Glutes (great for ladies), T-bar row machine, Ski machine and more!
The equipment and facilities are well-maintained. It'll be better if they offer the wet tissues dispenser that I see at some outlets, so that we can wipe our hands and equipment. I find there are too little bottles of sanitizer.
The washroom is clean, reasonably spacious and equipped with necessities (shower gel and hair dryer). The female washroom has two toilet cubicles and three shower cubicles. I'd recommend having more hangers installed in shower cubicles for our clothing.
Plenty of shelves and lockers are available, but the area is a little congested as they added one more shelf (understand it's necessary with more members visiting the gym). That area is too small to fit benches sadly.
Last but not the least, I had a good experience going through the PT trial with Kemar! Never expected to perspire so much in one hour, he really pushed me to my limits and taught me the correct form.
Variety of equipment: ‚≠ê‚≠ê‚≠ê‚≠ê‚≠ê
Staff: ‚≠ê‚≠ê‚≠ê‚≠ê‚≠ê
Cleanliness: ‚≠ê‚≠ê‚≠ê‚≠ê

text:
AF D‚ÄôArena truly stands out as the best. The facility is massive, spacious, and meticulously clean with a variety of equipment to meet every need. The huge functional area is a game-changer, providing ample space for workouts.

The washrooms are spotless, and the amenities offered, such as towels and chargers, really enhance the overall workout experience. What truly sets this gym apart, though, is the staff. They are extremely kind, always friendly, and genuinely care about the members. Shoutout to Colan, Ryan, and Hazwan!

Recently, the gym organized a trip to Batam, which was packed with fun activities for everyone. It was such a thoughtful gesture, and shows how much they value their community. The members here are like a family, making the gym experience wholesome and enjoyable.

Overall, this is hands down the best gym ever, with absolutely no complaints or bad remarks from me. Highly recommend!

I came here because I found out on TikTok that this gym has the calf raise machine which my home gym does not have. On top of having a wide variety of well-maintained equipment, the gym is spotlessly clean and very spacious. Towels and alcohol sprays can be easily found, but they also provide wet tissues to wipe down equipment. The toilets are clean, and they even have a hair dryer and a hygiene corner. They also provide a charging station with a multi charging cable and Wi-Fi. I come here at night and the view from the gym is an added bonus. This would definitely be my top choice for a home gym if I was staying nearby. If I had to name one thing that I would love to see here, it would be 10-20 kg straight barbells and 9kg dumbbells. :)

author: Shak
text:
I had to cancel my membership, before the first year contract is completed, due to medical reason and the admins had delayed this process with the explanation ‚Äúmanagement decision to review and approve cancellation may take time‚Äù. I have paid subscription for at least 4 months without even entering the facility, out of which 2 months are due to the management delaying to get back to me, and now they ask me to pay 100$ and close. Truly disappointing from such an established brand.

Regarding the facilities itself (Buangkok), when I sign up I was offered 1-hour free PT session, where the trainer taken up my entire hour trying to sell his service than helping me familiarize with basics. I gave this feedback, but not sure if that changes anything. I guess it's just ok ok facilities if you want to do things on your own, and for the first 4 weeks I went there, the equipments were available without waiting between 8 am to 10 am window (don't know about other times)..

Update 05th May 2024: The center had acknowledged that my membership was cancelled after I had paid $100 as early termination fee, however I have noticed in my bank statements that I was charged again for the membership fee in April and May 2024. I had reported this again to their official WhatsApp account in April which they did not respond, and today again where they gave a lame excuse of system issues causing unauthorized charging to my debit card, and I am told the two months fee will be credited back to me. I am glad that I had gone through my statements closely, if I hadn't then Anytime fitness would have continued to charge me.

I hope the anytime fitness upper management take action on this center's unprofessional handling of cancellations.

author: Melvin Ang
text:
There are only a few factors which define the success of gyms - location, affordability, variety of equipment, cleanliness and most importantly, the trainers.

They have checked all the boxes in my opinion and kudos to the entire management and staff of Anytime Fitness. Housing a gym within a commercial space at NTP is a move worth commending and applauding. Access to a gym right below my gym certainly help to cut traveling time. I can go in, get my workout done during lunch and be back in the office to continue my day.

Coming to trainers, Nash is definitely the go-to-guy. Experienced, accommodating yet genuinely serious about ensuring his clients enjoy and benefit from his sessions. Never boring yet constantly challenging oneself to breakthrough.

author: chok yenfei
text:
I recently had the pleasure of experiencing exceptional service from the staff, YUDA at Anytime Fitness, and I must say, it exceeded my expectations. From the moment I walked in, I was greeted with warm smiles and genuine enthusiasm from the staff members. They were incredibly knowledgeable about the facility and its offerings, taking the time to answer all of my questions and provide valuable guidance on achieving my fitness goals.

What truly stood out to me was their willingness to go above and beyond to ensure I felt comfortable and supported during my workouts. Whether it was assisting with equipment setup, offering helpful workout tips, or simply providing words of encouragement, the staff at Anytime Fitness made me feel like a valued member of the community.

Additionally, their commitment to cleanliness and safety measures was evident throughout the facility, which provided me with peace of mind during these uncertain times.

Overall, I cannot speak highly enough of the staff at Anytime Fitness. Their dedication to customer satisfaction and passion for promoting health and wellness truly sets them apart. I highly recommend this gym to anyone looking for a positive and empowering fitness experience.

author: Kelum Prasanna
text:
AFBV is the best gym i‚Äôve ever been to. Trust me i have tried them all in the area. Being located at a convenient part of the city and being open 24/7 its a perfect fit for everyone‚Äôs busy schedules. With an ambient interior and equipped in abundance AFBV is capable of hosting the fitness journey of many.
Moving on to staff, the most prominent guy I noticed was Abbas, he is dedicated to the clients while being so friendly and approachable. He sets an example to us how he maintains his body and behaviors. Such a gentleman.
Kester and Farah Norena  three other amazing souls who wouldn‚Äôt hesitate to help u with any matter in the gym. They will individualize ur workout routine rather than giving u a routine set. And the meal prep advice and supplementation advices are on point and goes hand in hand with their program , through social media. And always wanted to have biceps like kester but it‚Äôs going far away üòÖ
Finally our doggy Jax will inspect whether u do ur work correctly and give u cuddles and hugs if u are good. He is such a good boi and gives the best emotional support. Don‚Äôt forget to pet him if u go to AFBV üòä
Good job AFBV make my life easy ‚ù§Ô∏è

author: Rayson Neo
text:
I recently joined Anytime Fitness Buona Vista, and my experience has been nothing short of excellent. From the welcoming atmosphere to the state-of-the-art facilities, this gym has exceeded my expectations in every way.

1. Welcoming Atmosphere:
Upon entering the gym, I was immediately greeted by friendly staff who made me feel comfortable and valued. The positive and inclusive atmosphere at Anytime Fitness Buona Vista creates a motivating environment for every fitness enthusiast.

2. Clean and Well-Maintained Facilities:
One of the standout features of this gym is its commitment to cleanliness and maintenance. The equipment is top-notch and well-maintained, and the cleanliness of the facility reflects the staff's dedication to providing a hygienic workout space.

3. 24/7 Access:
The flexibility of having 24/7 access is a game-changer for those with busy schedules. It allows me to work out at any time that suits me, making it incredibly convenient and accommodating to my lifestyle.

4. Knowledgeable and Supportive Staff:
The trainers and staff at Anytime Fitness Buona Vista are not only friendly but also highly knowledgeable. They are always willing to offer guidance, answer questions, and provide valuable tips to help members achieve their fitness goals.

5. Varied Workout Options:
The gym offers a wide range of workout options, from cardio machines to free weights and functional training areas. The variety ensures that there's something for everyone, whether you're a seasoned athlete or just starting your fitness journey.

6. Community Engagement:
What sets Anytime Fitness Buona Vista apart is its emphasis on community. Regular events, classes, and challenges foster a sense of belonging among members, creating a supportive fitness community.

7. Convenient Location:
The gym's location in Buona Vista is convenient, making it easily accessible for both residents and those working in the area. Ample parking and proximity to public transportation add to the overall convenience.

In conclusion, Anytime Fitness Buona Vista is more than just a gym; it's a fitness community that prioritizes its members' well-being. Whether you're a fitness enthusiast or a beginner, this gym provides the tools and support needed to achieve your health and fitness goals.

I highly recommend Anytime Fitness Buona Vista to anyone looking for a positive and effective fitness experience.

text:
The best AF gym outlet I've ever been to! ü§©
- very spacious (despite having many equipment)
- stretching area has many accessories, floor is padded with soft mats (so no yoga mats)
- well lighted area throughout the gym (toilet facilities included)

- eg of equipment:
-- 4 power racks w/ island (ie 2 people can share this power rack, eg 1 squat + 1 DL)
-- 1 power rack (no island)
-- 2 Smith machines
-- 5 benches (adjustable)
-- 1 bench (fixed)
-- dumbbell rack up to 50 kg
(may get noisy during peak hours)

- built-in toilet facilities (uncommon for AF gym outlets)
-- 3 showers (1 designated for ladies)
-- 2 toilet cubicles (fancy looking + well ventilated, w/ well placed shelf + toilet roll + dustbin)
-- 1 changing room (1 full length mirror, 1 dustbin, 1 hanging rack, 1 small shelf)
-- small benches + shoe racks outside showers/toilet cubicles (thoughtful design!)

author: YH
text:
If you want to wear your masks at all times in the gym. Come here.

"WEAR YOUR MASK AT ALL TIME". I was instructed by the gym trainer in a rather unfriendly tone when I visited there for the first time. Most other gym trainers in other locations were very very friendly. That's fine really, but the wording is wrong. WEAR YOUR MASK WHEN YOU ARE RESTING sounds better and more reasonable. But this is also disputable according to Singapore Covid rules because:

For indoor activities, masks may be taken off when performing strenuous
activity or as part of a class requirement but will have to be put on after the completion of such strenuous sporting and physical activity/class and during rest breaks.

And technically the entire workout session in any gym can be considered a single activity albeit with short breaks in between sets. But that's besides the point.

If you want to wear your masks at all times in the gym and being treated like an army recruit. Come here.

text:
Be warned that if you report an issue, nothing will be done. Staff sent an invoice that overcharged me. When I feedbacked to staff that the invoice is wrong, they said they'll change it. Guess what? They didn't change it and I got charged the original amount a few months later üôÉ Subsequently I didn't even receive an apology.

This isn't even the first time they didn't take action. Previously I asked in person for my invoice to be sent to me so I can claim from my company, the staff said ok and got my details. I waited a week, no invoice was sent and I had to bump them for an update again.

What kind of gym staff are you hiring? It's really easy to pretend that you'll do something then not do it. Not to mention I saw one of them playing chess on their laptop during working hours.

author: HO
text:
I had a fantastic experience at Anytime Fitness Pasir Panjang! The gym is spacious, clean, and well-equipped, with friendly and helpful staff who create a welcoming environment.

My main goal was to lose belly fat and improve general fitness, and I‚Äôm thrilled with the results. Thanks to Shahrizan, my personal trainer, I lost 5.5kg during the training period (mid July- mid Nov 2024) and achieved a transformative change in how I feel. Shah assessed my fitness level thoroughly and designed a customized program tailored to my needs. He also guided me with a sustainable diet routine, ensuring the journey was effective and manageable.

The training was not just about the results but also about sustainability and long-term fitness habits. I highly recommend Anytime Fitness Pasir Panjang and Shah for anyone looking to embark on their fitness journey.

author: Keith Wong
text:
Firstly, the gym itself was clean and well-maintained. The equipment was in excellent condition, and there was plenty of space to move around and exercise comfortably. The gym also had a variety of equipment, including cardio machines, weight lifting machines, and free weights, which made it easy to switch up my workout routine.

Moreover, the staff at the gym was incredibly friendly and helpful. They were always willing to answer any questions I had and offer advice on how to improve my workouts. They also took the time to explain how to use the equipment correctly, which made me feel confident and safe while exercising.

Overall, my experience at the gym was exceptional, and I will definitely be visiting again. The clean and well-maintained gym, friendly staff, variety of equipment and group fitness classes, and excellent amenities made it an enjoyable and motivating experience. I highly recommend this gym to anyone looking for a great workout and a fun and welcoming atmosphere.

author: Ernest See
text:
Having been to this gym for almost two years, there are a few things to take note:

The gym equipment, especially the plates are quite musty and almost sticky. Just by touching the plates alone and your hand would turn brown or black. There is also a relatively sourish stink from some of the machines, like the pec deck fly machine or the lateral raise machine. There are also faults on machines that I have raised before a month or two back, where there are cables that are tearing, especially in the seated leg curl machine. It has still not been fixed, and its almost 3 months already.

Next are random leaks around the gym. If you look up in the deeper areas of the gym away from the entrances, you can see that there are water pipes that running in the ceiling. Some of these pipes leak frequently, especially around the lateral raise machine or the sled leg press. There can be watermarks on the floor near those areas and sometimes on the machine when the staff have not wiped the stains off the machine.

Lastly, would be the air conditioning. Since it is a mall, the aircon is actually rather decent in the gym during from about 9am to 11pm. However, beyond those timings the airconditioning would be turned off. There has been multiple complaints to the management saying that this issue would be resolved, yet nothing has been done for literal years. I have came to gym in wee hours in the morning (around 5-6am) and holy crap the temperatures are unbearable. It also gets rather humid since there is no ventilation within the gym at all, and people that gym during those timings will be found camping around the fans that are around in the gym. If you would like to gym in the early hours, please do not come to this gym.

However, I would also like to say that the staff are rather friendly and kind especially with new gym-goers. They also provide Ajwa Dates during the Ramadan period for Muslims that are gymming near or after the break fast period, which is a good sign to see. There are also many toilets around, about 7 toilets with 6 of them with shower facilities. The water coolers there are also functional, although the one nearest to the vending machine only has room temperature water as the cooling is not effective or has broken down.

text:
The gym is a short 5-minute walk away from Chinatown MRT.

The gym spans two floors. The first floor houses most of the equipment, and the second is largely a CrossFit area with 7 individual shower rooms (3 male, 2 female and 2 unisex). From the well-worn interior, it's apparent that the outlet is old.

Unlike most other Anytime Fitness outlets, the music selection here is tasteful and should satisfy the average gym patron. There are also lockers that are free to use.

My only gripe about this outlet is that the shower room doesn't have a stool of sorts so that patrons can put their belongings while showering. We'd have to hang out bags from hooks behind the door.

text:
3/5 ‚≠ê only because this place has basic enough gym equipment, aircon, and toilet/changing room w/in gym premises.
If you think a passing grade is "ok" for this gym, you're better off visiting the ActiveSG gyms - they're more affordable and have basically everything this gym already has (and more gym equipment), w/o eating up your 80$++ keyfob money upon registration and monthly gym membership fees.

The fans in this gym never seem to be used, and have their casings dismantled and left at a corner (regardless of time of day, or day of the month).

Have personally visited this gym multiple times on weekdays AND weekends on different months w/in the year and have not yet seen the fans being used at all.

If you want to experience what it's like exercising outdoors while being indoors, this is the gym to go to, because it can make you sweat quite easily w/o much exertion during your exercises.

A year ago, the toilets were pretty dirty but during my recent visits here, the toilet has been more tidied up. However, despite having built-in lockers/cabinets in each toilet for members to store their personal items, some are locked away.

Wrt my prior knowledge, the lockers were locked away during their renovation period TWO years ago to store miscellaneous/renovation/staff items, but ever since its reopening, they have not been unlocked for members to use, which poses a problem for members to store their items during peak periods. I have no idea what treasures lie beyond those locked doors, or if there is some unspoken evil trapped away during their renovation years back, that if unleashed, would wreck havoc upon the gym staff and members present at that moment in time.

Picture attached:
1) men's toilet sink (26 Dec 20)
2) dirty floors at different parts of gym (31 Dec 20)

text:
As anytime fitness outlets pop up across Singapore like I‚Äôm sure many are curious to compare how different outlets are like- and I have done exactly that in my little review over here.

First of all, excellent facilities- I counted a grand total of 6 squat racks. Half had the powerlifting platform.

There‚Äôs also 6/7 treadmills. 2 stair masters, 4 ellipticals. A solid number to fulfill the cardio needs of a large gym like this.

Oh! I was also surprised at the large space provided for changing needs. 6-7 bathrooms (fully equipped with a shower and a toilet and basin). It‚Äôs good for those who want to be squeaky clean.

Dumbbells are also aplenty. They use a older kind of dumbbell which is more elongated in shape (rather than being compact)- I can‚Äôt explain it but it makes sense trust me. Works just as well but not as lovely as the newer dumbbells.

Esoteric machines like for accessory movements are also available. Tricep push downs/bicep curls machine are here. üòÜüòÜ.

Huge space for functional fitness- think kettlebells, pull ups, yada yada. All the space in the world for your farmers carry.

author: Akhil
text:
Title: Terrible Experience - Avoid Anytime Fitness at All Costs!

I recently had the most disappointing and frustrating experience with Anytime Fitness, and I feel compelled to share it with others to prevent them from going through the same ordeal. Before joining the gym, they recommended that I take a 1.5-year membership without mentioning the existence of a notice period. They also assured me that they would assist in holding my membership during periods when I needed to be away from Singapore. Unfortunately, the reality turned out to be far from what was promised.

Due to unforeseen circumstances, I lost my job and had to return to India. As requested by Anytime Fitness, I provided them with all the required documentation, including a one way air ticket, a photo of my passport seal upon entering India, and a screenshot of my location on Google Maps. Despite complying with their demands, after the third month, they suddenly informed me that they couldn't extend my membership any further and resumed charging me.

To make matters worse, my membership had already expired six months ago, well beyond the initially agreed 1.5-year duration. When I requested to cancel my membership, they insisted on an additional paid month as a notice period, even though my financial situation was dire due to the lack of job opportunities and the high cost of living in Singapore. I explained my predicament, but they callously charged me twice, a total of $31, claiming that the cancellation couldn't be processed.

Aside from the horrendous customer service, the gym itself is far from satisfactory. The lack of sufficient equipment and the overwhelming number of people make it nearly impossible to have a productive workout, especially during peak hours. I strongly advise anyone looking for a gym in the Nordcomm or Gymbox area to consider alternative options, as the experience at Anytime Fitness is simply not worth the trouble.

Save yourself the frustration, disappointment, and unnecessary expenses by avoiding Anytime Fitness at all costs. There are definitely better gyms in the area that offer superior customer service and a more conducive workout environment.

author: Roshni Kapur
text:
I joined Anytime Fitness a few months ago and it has been great so far. The front desk staff at the Pasir Panjang outlet is really helpful and friendly. They have also assisted with requests when needed. The outlet is very spacious and well maintained with a good number of machines and free weights. The gym also has a positive and friendly vibe that encourages ones to work out regularly. While many corporate gyms in Singapore have hiked up their prices in recent years (and continue to increase), the membership rates at Anytime Fitness remain affordable and fixed.

Moreover, many corporate gyms close early on weekends or closed on public holidays and it becomes very inconvenient to get a proper workout. The 24/7 access at Anytime Fitness gives members the flexibility and ease to work out when their schedule permits. I would definitely recommend joining this gym.

author: altaf hussain Syed
text:
I've been a member of Anytime Fitness Gym Sunway Bigbox for couple of months now, and I can't sing enough praises for this fantastic gym! The facilities are top-notch, with state-of-the-art equipment, a clean and inviting environment, and convenient 24/7 access that fits perfectly into my busy schedule.

What truly sets this gym apart, though, is the exceptional staff, especially Personal Trainer Muhammad Naufal. His expertise in strength and mobility training has been a game-changer for me. Naufal's personalized approach ensures that every workout is tailored to my specific needs and goals. He pays close attention to form and technique, which has significantly improved my performance and prevented injuries.

Naufal's motivational style and positive attitude make each session enjoyable and rewarding. He pushes you to achieve your best while maintaining a supportive and encouraging atmosphere. Thanks to his guidance, I've seen remarkable improvements in my strength, flexibility, and overall fitness.

If you're looking for a gym that offers excellent facilities and outstanding personal training, Anytime Fitness Sunway Bigbox is the place to be. And if you want to elevate your fitness journey, I highly recommend working with Muhammad Naufal. He's truly the best in the business when it comes to strength and mobility training!

author: Daniel Ng
text:
Located within International Plaza. Do have a look at their IG on directions to get there because it's in a relatively obscure corner.

Pretty basic AF here with the basics. Dumbbells are hammer strength which go up in increments of 2kg. Otherwise, the gym is maintained well and equipments are all working well.

Toilets are also really nice and clean with 5 showers in the male toilet and plenty of room to put your belongings.

Overall the gym is well laid out and spacious. A good gym for gen pop and recreational lifters who work in the CBD. Not the best for serious lifters because you won't have a ton of leg equipment.

UPDATE 14/3:
The gym has expanded and added a few more power racks as well as lifting platforms, feels even more spacious now!

author: Ms.J Hassim
text: have been coming to this outlet pre reno and post reno. they did some great things with the toilet and shower yeah no big deal. but one I don‚Äôt get is they have this massive (what I‚Äôd call it) functional training space at L2.. yes I get it, it‚Äôs gym rules to have proper footwear when training, especially when dealing with weights. here‚Äôs the thing: some people train barefoot as part of their conditioning. it‚Äôs backed by evidence that barefoot training have it‚Äôs positive side. previous management are all about supporting their members in their journey. the new people from of current management though, not only they are the only AF staffs that don‚Äôt smile to their members, they‚Äôre almost like snobs. today i got told off I need to wear shoes when training at L2. Sure, I was only doing some ATG squats, dead hangs, cossacks and i probably weigh 135lbs so perhaps I am a threat to myself /s. I wore my shoes thereafter. No big deal i thought, except it was. For the last 10 times I been there, I‚Äôve been bare footing whilst training not until 19/1/24, right. Soon, came a dude who was in Slippers and the footwear police didn‚Äôt come and tell him off to wear his shoes so I reckon it‚Äôs more like; If you‚Äôre gonna do barefoot, don‚Äôt let the staff see you?. In hindsight perhaps they felt it‚Äôs their duty to enforce club rules, don‚Äôt know. It differs between different staffs too I guess. Since not everyone‚Äôs a footwear police. the Guy PT didn‚Äôt bat an eye the few times he saw me barefooted? I‚Äôve been to a few other AF branches, old and new and all ran by different groups. all of them smiled and greeted any members that walked in their gym.. Especially the guys not too far from their neighbourhood, AF Bugis. I loved coming to UCS branch cause they had solid racks for people who train functional and bodyweight like me (they have a gymnastics ring which they didn‚Äôt dispose off from the previous guys) and that was a plus, big time. they didn‚Äôt bother me much with barefooting, even when they did that one time, they were polite. and EXCUSE ME, we‚Äôre the paying members of your gym, if you were to reinforce footwear at least do it politely. Now I‚Äôm not even planning to come back and hope I tapped in enough at other branch so my membership gets converted to others, anywhere BUT UCS. Good luck maintaining your old members. slowly starting to see less familiar faces in that branch. whilst a gym as small as Queensway shopping still have the familiar faces from pre pandemic.

author: Karen Cheng
text:
Tried to use the gym. After about 2 months of my last visit. Found that it is closed and in the process of moving to another location.

Called the management to check the whereabout of my stuffs - a nice pair of Nike shoes cosing more than $200, towels and small exercise accessories - in the locker. The staff was fully aware that I was storing my stuffs overnight in the locker and had even assigned the locker - one that is not a convenient location - to me. Initially Rick said that if Bernnie is aware I was using the locker to storey stuff overnight, he would have kept the stuff for me. 15 min later, he called me back and informed me they did not keep anything from the lockers and they were most probably taken by the contractors and denied defensively and rudely that it was not their fault as I should have read the notice put up on the move. I reasoned that I was not aware and could not have read the notice since I had not Bern back to the gym for weeks.

Loss of my things aside and is small matter. What annoyed me was his too-fast to deny any responsibility attitude with no apology.  As he said , if Bernnie was aware I was keeping my stuff overnight in the locker. He would have kept for me. The fact was he was aware.

I feel they had not managed the move well. Is it so difficult to keep the remaining stuffs from the lockers of their members for a few months? Upon aware of the outcome despite his earlier statement that they should be kept, he changed his stand 180 degree and pointed all his 5 fingers at me.

I think I will not be patronizing the gym anymore despite its closeness to my office.

Totally disappointed with their attitude and management.

author: „Åì„Å∞„ÇÑ„Åó „É¨„Ç™
text:
The gym is ok.
But they have some of the worst gym bullies there. One of them asked to share the equipment (for chest workout) but in an unfriendly tone, while he was doing back, which was fine. So I let him use, and when it's my turn again, it was my last set and after I did a few reps, I wanted to drop the weight and continue to do a few more reps but he wouldn't let me. He said it's his turn. Omg. Then after he finished that set, he came to me and asked "what's your name? what's your problem?" Omgggg
Then another day I encountered another guy. He just "growls" a lot when he's working out, very loudly that the whole gym can hear him. And he puts the bar on the metal racks very loudly too. And when he's using other equipments, he also lets go at the highest point such that the metals just clash super loudly. It's like he wanna break the equipments. When he asked to share the dumbbell or equipment, he would say something like "can I share this since you are looking at your phone?" Helloooo, everyone needs to rest between set. Looking at handphone to reply messages for 30seconds is normal. And rest between sets can last for 1 to 2 minutes also. Why can't I look at handphones? You can ask to share and I don't mind sharing. But the attitude is bad.

And the water flow from the sinks at the basin and water dispenser is extremely slowww.
Also, the cleaner likes to vacuum and mop behind u and the vacuum and mop would just hit ur feet. And u can tell it's intentional coz he can totally see u standing there and it happens many times. I don't understand why he could not just say "excuse me" or just simply not mop so close. The fact that it looks intentional is really irritating.
And the cleaning of toilet and changing room always happens during 6-7pm where it's usually when most people come to gym and get changed...

Starting next week I think I will purposely take a bus to the next nearest AF branch to work out (this branch is just opposite my office and is super convenient for me but I'd rather travel to gym).

author: Carol
text:
Abbas is wonderful! I can't say enough good things about him. We signed up for the PT session for a unique goal - to kickstart "gyming" and learn the correct form for different workouts. I really appreciate that Abbas catered his sessions to our needs and designed a program to work towards our goal, instead of fitting us to any set template. He really helped us achieve what we look for at the end of the 10 sessions and now we are officially onto our gyming journey!
During the sessions, Abbas is patient, encouraging, and thorough in his explanation. He would correct our forms and also explain the anatomy behind it to help us better understand. He always encourages questions and helped us solve all problems we face in different exercises.
He is also patient and never rush us during the training, going deep into each concept and give us multiple sets to make sure we learnt the technique thoroughly and do it right, sometimes even going beyond the scheduled duration just to teach us more.
He is also gentle and encouraging, which really helped us overcome the 'fear' of being a newbie to train in gyms. Now I am no longer afraid of going to gyms! He really motivates me to continue gyming and start living a healthier lifestyle.
All in all, I would (and will) definitely recommend anyone who needs PT to come to Abbas' class. It was a invaluable experience!

author: JW Yeo
text:
I was a member between early 2022 to late that year. During that time, I hired a trainer by the name of Ryan Bai. He was late, rude and frequently spent more time on his phone than training people. I fired him after 3 months but already paid more than 3000 SGD in fees.

AF CCK compensated me less than 1000 SGD in membership fees but not the rest because as a third party contractor, he's not considered an AF employee.

Because of work purposes, I had no choice but to keep signing with AF in order to move around freely in Singapore. In the last year, I tried repeatedly to contact AF accounts and marketing to get the additional 2000 back in terms of membership fees.

Now as part of AF woodlands, I get chased every month when there are late fees. I also get annoyed text messages on WhatsApp everytime I'm late for fees. I paid more than 4k SGD in total for 2 years of membership. For all the money I paid, I get this sort of treatment.

I wanted to avoid trouble and simply train my body. But honestly speaking, Gymboxx, ActiveSG and SAFRA have never given me this sort of trouble. The so called gym trainer, didn't even bother to plan things or teach anything. I trained myself via youtube.
source_file: Anytime Fitness Choa Chu Kang Centre_reviews.csv

Really dirty. Was charged $25 as a visitors for a gross gym and rude service.  To be charged so much and not have a half decent space to work out is a joke. I‚Äôm moving to Singapore and do not recommend you go here as a local or a tourist. Clean your equipment! Disgusting.

Because I can reply to the passive aggressive comment that was just left by a staff member I will leave it here.

If the gym is so clean than why are there 2-3 other RECENT Reviews stating otherwise? One written 5 days before mine? And yes I was at the time a tourist visitor. But this location does not live up to Anytime fitness standards  (which I have been to in MULTIPLE countries) it is  for this reason why I was upset about having to pay the $25. But to be fair I should have walked around the gym before paying. It‚Äôs my fault for having faith that the gym would live up to decent hygiene expectations ESPECIALLY IN SINGAPORE. This should be a well maintained gym considering where it‚Äôs located and how ‚Äúnew‚Äù it is. It‚Äôs even more appalling because the gym is new you would expect it to be good quality. Not to mention there is little to no staff member present and the one that was there was abrasive and rude ( also noted in OTHER people‚Äôs comments) you guys clearly need to up your standards people have commented saying the bathrooms made them want to puke so my apologies for not going into further details about the disgusting state of the gym. I hope for Corprates sake you guys improve the gym and keep it well maintained and CLEAN otherwise I‚Äôm sure these types of post will continue (hence the last few). Thanks for responding though at least you are doing one thing right!

text:
This is one solid gym. It's packed with free weights and machines while being spacious. Never had issues navigating awkwardly.

Quite unlike other gyms which are saturated with cardio machines, this one's a real gangster with what I think is the right mix. No wonder almost everyone here is toned.

Also heard from the staff that the gym would be bringing in new equipment, which is exciting. Shows that it's actively improving.

Never expected that a gym could be so clean too. I have a sensitive nose, and couldn't pick up the usual odd gym-ish scent throughout my time working out.

Gym staff is chill yet professional too. Juenie was the one who helped explain processes and gave the gym tour to me.

author: Surekha Pawar
text:
I joined gym in March this year, the gym is neat and clean, thanks to housekeeper Sufi whom I always see at work.

I got Maple for my first intro PT session and I am very happy that I signed her for further sessions. Her training style is varied with functional, HIIT, strength training with progressive overload, compound movements, pyramid style etc she really keeps workout interesting and gives weekly homework as well.

She is very patient and encouraging and always answers my workout related questions with enthusiasm, which is very helpful in understanding what muscle group is being used and to make a good mind-muscle connection. I have trained previously with 3 male trainers from other gyms and even though so young she is definitely as good as them or dare I say much better.

Thanks a lot Maple for the workout guidance you provide and I hope with you I can achieve good results even though I have many health issues.

author: Hans Chan
text:
I'm surprised this gym got a streak of bad reviews previously? I think this gym has the most barbell racks I've seen in a AF gym (4 racks and 2 barbell stands on other end, and 2 deadlift platforms. And they have assault bike and concept2 rower as well. Perfect for people into free weight/power lifting/cross trainings. I can't review for machines cuz i don't care about those. Only hope to have is more benches for free weights. Most of the time I literally only see 1 available bench for dumbbell area.

Toilet is clean and 1 for each gender. Really like the convenience of this location as well.

text:
My six months of training with Haz at the gym have paid off tremendously. My goal in starting to train with Haz was to increase my muscular mass. At first, I was hesitant, but now I'm pleased I made the commitment. Haz is extremely well-versed and experienced, and he takes the time to carefully consider my needs before designing a program that pushes me yet is within my capabilities. He is really encouraging and helpful, and I can always count on him to challenge me to give more than I thought I had in me.

My strength and self-assurance have increased dramatically over the past six months. I can't thank Haz enough for all his support and advice. He has been the driving force behind my physical and personal growth.

I think Haz is the best gym trainer out there and would suggest him to anybody seeking to get in shape. He is amazing.

text:
Not a fan of the lack of maintenance of equipment, alongside the fact that if you'd like to refer a friend in you'd have to constantly arrange an appointment during office hours.

In theory, office workers only have time to work out before and after office hours so the theory is kinda flawed.

Additionally, the gym has a strict policy of not allowing you to play music with their speakers.

The gym recently installed new prism+ TVs that plays music that intermittently cuts off, which is a huge disturbance and pain in the @** if you ask me.

Driving to other gyms in the future like Woods Square's anytime fitness instead.

Disappointing.

author: Sihan Goi
text: One of the better Anytime Fitness gyms around. There are 2 power racks with attached platforms, another dedicated platform, another 2 half racks, plenty of bars and bumper plates to go around, including 1 Eleiko bar and 2 hex bars, lots of plate loaded and cable/pulley machines, an open area for warmups/battling ropes/sled work/heavy bags, and the usual cardio machines. There's also a lone C2 rower, which is nice to see since most other AF gyms seem to favour water rowers instead. Facilities wise, there's a unisex changing/shower room, but no toilets (you'll have to go out to the main building toilet for that. Crowd wise, I was there from about 730am to 9am. Initially it was quite empty, but past 8am it started getting crowded, and all the racks were used. Parking at the area is kinda confusing since there are so many different buildings in the area (the gym is at Helios), but ultimately they all share the same basement carpark, so just go inside and follow the signs to Helios.

text:
Pros :
Very friendly staff. Well equipped gym. Tidy and clean. Convenient and accessible location. They used to play gym music openly thru a speaker which sometimes some gym users might abuse it by blasting their music out loud esp during wee hrs when there's no staff around. Now, they play it thru a TV instead and at a much lower volume so i think thats a very good move because these days gym-goers mostly have their own music that they listen to with their own earbuds ect.

Cons :
Not too sure about other franchise but i think this place might be a little bit too pricey for its membership. Why i felt so is because this place has no built-in toilet nor shower place and if compared to other outlets that has all those facilities, the price is more or less the same hence making this outlet seem pricier. Also this place is much smaller compared to its neighbouring outlet. But this is just my honest thoughts and only grouse i have is the pricing. Thats all. Apart from that, this gym along with its staff and management has been awesome!

text: I'm very happy with the onboarding. From signing up to being offered a one-off training session. I've read other reviews and agree there's a great vibe at AF Tanjong Pagar. It's clean, the layout is excellent, and the staff I've met are kind. Shah explained the sign-up process smoothly. Jay, one of the PTs, gave an excellent one-off training session (encouraging you with the right push) but without any pressure to sign-up for anything. You simply feel supported. üëçüèº I'm one of those who are a little nervous returning to the gym after X years... but I feel comfortable at AF Tanjong Pagar. Cheers to the AF Tanjong Pagar team (and extra kudos to the people who keep the gym clean).

author: Feng Yi Chew
text:
This relatively new gym is well-maintained and very clean, with polite and attentive staff.

I personally prefer AF outlets that use the Hammer Strength/ Life Fitness brands of equipment, and was glad to note that this was the case here. There are toilets on both the first and second floors, which is convenient.

I felt that the first floor was rather cramped with machines and racks/platforms in close proximity to each other, and would urge gym users to be mindful of their surroundings especially when racking/removing weight plates. The low ceiling also made it feel a tad claustrophobic.

The second floor is a lot more roomy, though - chest day gymbros would particularly appreciate the spacious dumbbell area and multiple benches upstairs!
source_file: Anytime Fitness Ang Mo Kio South_reviews.csv

author: Tabasco Guzzler
text: Decent gym with a nice city view. Service is inconsistent: brand ambassador Shakir was welcoming & friendly at first - but suddenly turned cold & hostile for no reason. When I politely asked him to help me find a piece of equipment, he was super unfriendly & deliberately slow to assist. I thanked him with a smile, but he was silent & glared at me. A gym user who heard me asking for help was kind enough to find the missing object. Fortunately, Aliah @ front desk & Natalia the trainer were nice & forthcoming. If not for Shakir's weird behaviour which made me feel uneasy - I would have posted 5 stars!

text:
I had great experiences at this gym, however, a recent situation happened to me that I had to give it a low 1 star.

So, I forgotten to bring my KeyFOB with me, and usually if it‚Äôs during staffed hours, they will manually registered me into the gym, no problem. However, today, they turned me away and said that they have a new ‚ÄúNo KeyFOB, No entry‚Äù policy. I tried to reason with the staff but he did not give any wiggle room.

I find this completely unreasonable. It‚Äôs during staffed hours, it‚Äôs a super simple process and you will be doing your customer a huge favour. And don‚Äôt you want happy customers? I just don‚Äôt understand why can‚Äôt this be done.

Besides the adorable cleaning uncle, the management and logic of this gym is questionable and frustrating.

@Hillv2AF‚ÄôsManagement, please consider lifting this policy at your gym. You‚Äôll be doing us tired gym goers a huge help, when we made the effort to go to your gym and not be turned away. Thanks.

author: Aaron Ritchie
text:
I've just moved into the Pasir Panjang area and I am quite happy that Anytime Fitness Pasir Panjang is my new local gym. When I walked in on my first session, I was greeted by the friendly William who recognised I was new to this particular club. He offered by a guided tour of all the facilities to put me at ease and know where everything is.

The facilities are plentiful and spacious. There are three distinct areas to the gym; a cardio machine section, a padded class studio, and an expansive free weights room. The weights room has four squat racks, and plenty of weights to go around, as well as two rowing machines and two air bikes if you're looking to throw some cardio into your weights routine. The padded class studio is a great place to go and work on your core or do some stretches in a quiet environment (when there's no classes happening).

The gym is located just a short walk down from Pasir Panjang MRT station on the Circle Line.

text: Visiting this as an Australian Anytime Fitness member. Rather small gym but equipment selection is excellent. There was a wide cable machine in an otherwise tight space (Very happy that this was available!). Not easy to social distance within the confines. One major critique I had was how members would maintain the sanitary conditions of the shared equipment. There were baskets with sanitising spray and microfibre towels attached to the machines. The reusing of these towels was what made me feel extremely uncomfortable. (How often are they washed and replaced?) Most other AFs I had visited in Singapore (and in Australia) use disposable wipes. Yes, they aren‚Äôt as environmentally friendly but considering the current pandemic conditions we are in, I suppose that would be a better trade off than the common microfibre towel wipes.

author: Aileen Vitug
text:
Anytime Fitness NEX has been one of the most disappointing gym experiences I've ever had. Despite the 24/7 access being advertised as a major perk, the facility is often overcrowded, there's a queue in using the equipment during peak hours, making it nearly impossible to get a decent workout. Equipment is frequently out of order, and the machines that do work are either outdated or poorly maintained. Cleanliness is another major issue ‚Äì sweat-streaked benches, dirty floors  are regular occurrences.

The staff seems indifferent at best; they're hardly ever available for help and, when they are, they‚Äôre not very welcoming. I signed up and their staff, Grace, promised my partner 1 free month of membership for referring me. She assured us this even if we didn't ask for it but at the end she denied ever saying it, because we didn't have any proof, so we cannot also trust the staff keeping their word. I regret having signed up in this gym, I don't like being lied to.

Anytime Fitness NEX feels like a rip-off and far from the good experience they claim to provide. I‚Äôd recommend looking elsewhere if you‚Äôre serious about your fitness. Before making a mistake of signing up on this branch.

author: Meizi Lim
text:
This place don‚Äôt even deserve 1 star.

Signed up back when they first started their outlet here. The reviews here about Jasmine and her management team is relatable to my experience:

1. Back when safe-entry was implemented, her device was faulty, hence many members were stuck outside during unstaffed hours. She called me to reprimand me for opening the door for the members (yes, i understand AF‚Äôs tailgating issue, but they were all regulars I‚Äôve seen, and they were obv stuck outside >10mins seeking for my help). Faulty device issue has already been raised before this, and nothing has been done. Instead, Jasmine demanded me to pass MY phone to each of the members to ask them to scan in manually in the middle of my workout????? (don‚Äôt even have the courtesy to allow me to finish my reps).

2. Few weeks later, I was the only few in the gym. Jasmine called me AGAIN, to ask me open the door for her contractor as no staffs were around. Hello??? I‚Äôm not a staff there???? This is a violation of customer‚Äôs PDPA, used for unintended purposes?
Also, Isn‚Äôt it contradicting to point 1?

3. Jasmine replied to the reviews saying they‚Äôre fake accounts trying to bring down her gym. Firstly, even if their records wasn‚Äôt shown in your system, members of other AF outlets are entitled to leave a review too. Secondly, always viewing from a victimised POV instead of thinking of ways to improve shows how you got your 2.6stars on google.

No, don‚Äôt tell me you can‚Äôt find my name in your system because I‚Äôve decided to transfer to other branch who deserves the monthly fees better. Good luck with your 2.6 star gym.

author: Paul Chin
text:
Run away at all cost, when you see this Anytime Fitness branch gym centre at 134 Jurong gateway. It's frustrating and nasty when they don't allow you to end your contract as agreed upon during the sign-up period. They will play dumb when you want to terminate the contract whenever the minimum contact period has met. Having to wait until the last month and visit them in person to cancel seems unnecessary. They should honor the specific period you signed up for and make the cancellation process more convenient for their members.
What the other members commented here in Google reviews about Jasmine (probably is a fake name pretend by a guy) is true. They will purposely mislead you not wanting you to cancel your membership period on time, try to drag longer than it supposed to end, let you pay extra for the membership. And mocking you say that if you don't like installment, why don't you pay lump sum amount when you signed up with them? This is how they treat their customers? This is how they run business? We hope they are no more victims. Anyone who have gotten this kind of treatment, should go to CASE to report them.. This kind of business should not be existed anymore in Singapore.

author: Chuin Ann
text:
I have been a member of this gym for 12 months, and my experience has been nothing short of disappointing. The facility is poorly maintained, with rusty equipment and chipped dumbbells that are not only unsightly but also a potential safety hazard. The gym plates are often dirty, adding to the overall lack of cleanliness. The uneven gym floor is another major issue, making it unsafe for workouts.

The poor air conditioning only adds to the discomfort, making the gym environment unbearable at times. Despite these glaring issues, the management shows no interest in maintaining the facility or addressing these concerns.

Additionally, their treatment of existing customers is extremely unsatisfactory. After my 12-month contract ended, I hoped to renew my membership at a better rate. Instead, I was informed that my membership auto-renews without any end, and they refused to offer me a better price, while new members are given promotional rates.

When I raised these concerns, the staff's response was dismissive, asking, "how do you wish to go on about this," rather than offering any solutions. Ultimately, when I decided to terminate my membership, they showed no interest in retaining me as a customer and simply told me to send an email.

Overall, this gym does not value its members, and I cannot recommend it to anyone looking for a well-maintained facility and respectful customer service.

author: JY
text:
Ella is not doing any good to this organization. Frankly, she is totally not suitable to do sales.

I enquired about joining the gym as a friend referred. My friend told me he can get 1 month free if I join by quoting him. I found out that currently, Anytime Fitness is waiving off the joining fees. However, for the outlet in Nortpoint City, for them to honor one free month for my friend who referred, I have to pay joining fees.

I am upset as they are using my money to give one month free to my friend. This is totally not right.

To me, Ella couldn't handle objections. Doesn't even bother selling the benefits of the gym.

I really hope the owner can really consider if Ella is suitable for the job. Clearly, she is pushing customers away. There are so many other gyms in Singapore. If you don't show interests in having my business, you will lose it completely. Not only she gave Anytime Fitness Northpoint City a bad name, she doesn't represent Anytime Fitness well.

She made me totally don't want to consider joining Anytime Fitness. She made Anytime Fitness lose a customer who is ready and eager to join.

Seriously the management should really consider if she is suitable for the role. Frankly, she does not represent Anytime Fitness well. Any potential leads if handled by her will also turn cold.

Suggest the boss to use mystery shoppers to test the response of their staff. In this competitive world, not having the right sales personnel will be more damaging than not have any sales personnel.

text:
I've had close to 20 personal training sessions with Zul and it has been life-changing. He's successfully converted me from a non-gym-goer, who knew next to nothing about weight training and using the gym equipment to someone who is highly motivated to exercise. It's easily the best part of my day.

Zul has also gone the extra mile to help me relook my daily food intake and nutrition to enhance my performance at the gym.

What I like most is knowing that he's not someone who builds his muscles and calls it a day. Zul's dedication towards fitness and personal training lies in his knowledge of the field. I know that he is constantly learning and taking up related courses to do his job better and for the benefit of his clients such as myself.

Zul carries an easy and friendly disposition - the same can be said of all the staff at Anytime Fitness ACE The Place CC. Their infectious easy-going personality makes the place accommodating and warm, and my experience at the gym pleasant.

author: Kevin Lee
text:
Anytime Fitness Chai Chee is a fantastic gym that offers everything you need for a great workout experience. The facilities are top-notch, with a wide range of well-maintained equipment that caters to all types of fitness goals. Whether you're into strength training, cardio, or functional exercises, you'll find the right tools to get the job done.

The cleanliness of the gym is another highlight. The staff takes great care in ensuring that the space is always spotless, which makes working out here a pleasant experience. The layout is also well-organized, with plenty of space between machines, so you never feel cramped, even during busy hours.

What I appreciate most about Anytime Fitness Chai Chee is the convenience it offers. Being open 24/7, it allows me to fit in my workouts at any time that suits my schedule. This flexibility is a huge plus for anyone with a busy lifestyle.

Overall, Anytime Fitness Chai Chee is an excellent gym with great facilities, a clean and well-maintained environment, and a friendly atmosphere. I highly recommend it to anyone looking for a reliable and convenient place to work out.

Things to improve in my opinion:

2) Men's toilet needs to be maintained better as the cubicle and urinals are always stinky. (I am not sure about the ladies restroom). Setting up some dedicated changing rooms will be great as well.
3) The A/C in the gym are always inconsistent, some days are cold, some days it is just warm and stuffy (encountered a few times of my visits during peak hours, 5pm - 7.30pm).

author: Sihan Goi
text:
Large and spacious, with separate spaces for free weights/plate loaded machines, other weight machines/cardio equipment, and a large room for group classes. The shower area is one of the better ones for AF too. Also, I like the fact that upgrades have been made over the years. Currently, there are 4 power racks, 2 back to back half racks, 2 lifting platforms, multiple adjustable benches, weight plates/bumper plates, multiple Olympic barbells (Ziva and Hammer Strength ones that spin, and a few old ones), hex bars, EZ bars, and heavier dumbells up to 47.5kg. Many of these are quite new. There's also a C2 rower, water rower, assault bike, and many spin bikes. I can't list all the equipment, just look at my pictures. There were a few things previously preventing it from getting 5 stars IMHO, but they've all been addressed one by one over the years, so it gets 5 stars from me now. The only bad things I can think of is the fact that you need to be relatively quiet while lifting. I've gotten complained before a couple years ago while setting the barbell down a bit too loudly, but bumper plates and platforms would kinda address this. Also, some of the staff aren't very familiar with the equipment when I had some questions. Other than that, it's awesome!

Update: I had to drop this to 4 stars, because despite the platform, bumper plates, and new hammer strength Olympic spin bars, you apparently can't do Olympic weightlifting here. I got complained by staff for dumping the bar from overhead, despite all the equipment being designed specifically to be dumped from overhead, because it was "too loud". There's no point getting the best equipment in the world if you can't use them the way they were designed to be used.

author: Theron Seow
text:
Having prior injuries, slipdisc of the L5S1 and scoliosis I was wary of the types of exercises that I am able to do. Being underweight my whole life and tired feeling limited by my weaknesses, I decided to take a shot at Anytime Fitness Woodlands Ace The Place CC under personal trainer/manager Nurin. After only one month I've gained 2kg in weight and muscle mass. More than I've ever gained in a short period. The training was tailored specifically to work around my injuries and allowed me to hit a couple of PRs. I no longer feel any back pain due to the improved overall fitness, and have become more confident even to partake in their monthly fitness challenge.

The gym's full time trainer and staff, Nicole and Addina are very welcoming as well, always checking in my wellbeing and sharing tips to improve performance. They encouraged and helped boost a holistic environment.

10/10 would recommend!

author: S. Fatimatuzzahrah S. Abdullah A.Q
text:
I go between here and their gym at Marsiling CC only because the staffs here are respectful and approachable. Also the condition of the gym is great. The best part about this gym is that there's a shower room and the loo that is well kept and maintained. My favourite hour to go is in the early hours at about 7 AM where there's literally no one and you can use all of the equipment, uninterrupted.

Now while we're at it, I have to commend on the Coach Ismail's HIIT & Boxing classes held there every Friday. This is a class NOT TO BE MISSED. His class definitely make you break a sweat even for a newbie like myself and his years of experience really shines through. He is not only understanding and highly emphatic, he is also such an encouraging and motivating individual which is helpful for those who comes to his class as they varies from all different fitness level. So kudos, to the Manager at AF ACE on having him for those classes because it shows that he knows his clients. I hope this class will never go away.

author: Yuki Kino
text:
earlier today i made a phone call to the buangkok branch to enquire about my brother's membership issue to know more about the problem and honestly speaking i feel that the staff was very unprofessional.
I only called to enquire and just to check on how to the membership works then afterwards i explain on the membership that my brother had and ask on how to cancel. the man on the phone with me had the audacity to mention that i was blaming  the company when i was just purely asking and explaining about my situation.  the audacity of that staff made me so speechless and disappointed as i was only trying to solve the problem on the cancellation of the membership instead of blaming him BUT he was pointing fingers at me.
Not only that, prior before when my brother sign up for this membership at the midtown outlet, the staff who recommended this contract did NOT highlight the important parts of the contract. I understand that it is part of my brother's fault for not reading the contract BUT as a service provider they should be more professional and highlight the important part of the contract, example like the rules on cancelling the membership and the fact that the membership is auto renew monthly.
ultimately, i hope that all the service provider staffs will be more professional when handling their clients by highlighting all the important points in the contract AND explain more in-depth to avoid confusions like this in the future.

author: Michael
text:
I‚Äôve always appreciated how Anytime Fitness promotes itself as being a part of the community. However, I‚Äôm deeply disappointed with the branch at Bukit Timah Shopping Centre. It seems that the business owners here are more focused on profits than truly caring for the community they‚Äôre part of.

The poorly waterproofed toilets have caused significant damage to tenants downstairs, with water leaks and even ceilings falling. This isn‚Äôt just an inconvenience; it‚Äôs a serious issue affecting the livelihoods of other businesses.

As a brand that prides itself on community, I urge you to take responsibility and fix this problem promptly. Please show that you care for the people and businesses around you, not just your own bottom line.

author: Vynsnt Ymmnwl
text:
Review: Inefficient Shower Allocation

The gym has a rather puzzling issue with the shower stall setup at this gym. Despite having more male members than female, and a consistent trend of more men being present at any time of the day, the shower facilities seem disproportionately allocated. Out of four stalls, two are reserved exclusively for women, while the remaining two are designated as unisex.

This arrangement leads to clear inefficiencies. The two female-exclusive stalls often appear underutilized, while the unisex stalls‚Äîused primarily by men due to their majority‚Äîtend to experience overcrowding and longer wait times. It feels like an unfair allocation of resources, where half of the facilities are reserved for a smaller demographic, leaving the majority to share the rest.

A more logical approach would be to allocate three stalls as unisex and one exclusively for females, or to adopt a dynamic system that adjusts based on demand during peak hours. It‚Äôs a shame, as the gym overall offers great amenities, but this lack of consideration for actual usage patterns detracts from the experience. A simple adjustment could make things much more equitable and efficient for everyone.

author: dominicpoh
text:
Unfortunately, my worst experience as an AF member. Membership was transferred here since I moved around here; I‚Äôve been with AF since 2017. Been to many outlets but this is the first time im leaving a negative review.

Pros
1. Location. Inside northpoint.
2. 6 racks.
3. Huge space.

Cons
1. Since it‚Äôs within a mall, I believe much of their aircon is dependent on the mall‚Äôs aircon source (?). For early gym goers like myself, the gym is a sauna. Many of us will be camping around fans in between sets lol.

2. Equipment. Spoilt. Rusty. Smelly. To name a few. One the machine was spoilt throughout the duration I‚Äôve been a member with them (around 2 months). Some of the accessories at the cable machine is really‚Ä¶ smelly

3. No customer service at all. I‚Äôm not usually particular about this but it really feels like the staffs there are ‚Äúbusiness-centric‚Äù. After joining, they straight away increased my membership price due to 8% GST though my previous outlet absorbed it lol. Received another email for price hike again this month. When I transferred to other outlets previously, l felt very welcomed, they even offered mini welcome gifts. Staffs will always smile and wave goodbye when you leave. Nothing of such here haha unless probably you know the staffs personally. In conclusion, very prompt in their finance management.

I usually mind my own business and gym, but the constant price hike really doesn‚Äôt justify the quality and service.

author: Julia
text:
I've been visiting AFBTC for the last two years since its opening for 3-5 times per week, and the gym management has consistently been great at maintaining cleanliness and equipment upkeep. I've been to other AF gyms across Singapore and I can say honestly that this gym has done a great job creating a friendly and conducive environment for working out.

1. Clean area: The cleaners are here daily to keep the space clean, whether it's mopping the floor or wiping down the equipment as needed. There are self-service antibacterial sprays and cloths in every corner of the gym for us to wipe down after each use as well. The toilets are great as well, definitely cleaner than other public ones nearby (yes I've dropped by the gym just to use the toilet before, because Coronation Plaza's toilet is nasty sometimes).

2. Friendly staff: Employees like Carmen, Jamie, and Nadia have been nothing but helpful every time I ask about something. Not sure what's with the complaints from a couple of recent reviews, but RF gyms including AFBTC are literally the only AF gyms where the staff bother greeting you lol.

3. Equipment upkeep: The equipment variety at this gym has been pretty decent considering the size of the gym, and they have everything I need to get a good workout. Sometimes it's a little inconvenient when a couple of machines are down e.g. the one of the treadmills/lat pulldown machine sometimes goes under maintenance for 1 week, but it's still fairly reasonable. They also add new types of machines every few months, which is pretty nice.

4. Respectful gym members: More than 95% of the folks I've met in this particular outlet have been very polite. I've been to gyms where people interrupt you in between sets - none of this BS here. The staff here take gym etiquette seriously and so do the members. Unfortunately there were a couple of times where someone didn't rerack their stuff after working out - hope those people's pillows stay warm on both sides all night.

5. Extra perks: Members' Days are something to look forward to every couple of days per month - I never really remember when they are but when it happens, it's like a surprise reward for coming down to the gym. The main perk I really love about this gym is the female toilet though. It's always well-stocked with sanitary pads in case of any "emergencies". It goes to show the extra step they've taken to care for their members. I don't know any non-RF AF gyms that do that. Sure, some commercial gyms offer better perks, but they don't offer the same level of convenience at the same price range.

I'm not being paid to write this, and I didn't use chatgpt for this either. I genuinely enjoy coming to this gym, and I hope they stay around for a longgggg time.

author: Joel Gwey
text:
I can't say enough positive things about Anytime Fitness Bukit Timah Central. It's incredibly convenient, just a short 10 minute walk from Botanic Garden MRT station. The gym equipment is top-notch and well maintained, which is a huge plus for me. Despite the slightly smaller size, the cozy and chill atmosphere really adds to the overall experience.

One standout feature is the fantastic music playlist they have. Not only do they play great music, but they also allow members to add their own songs to the shared playlist, something I haven't seen in other Anytime Fitness clubs. This personal touch makes each workout session even more enjoyable.

The staff at AFBTC deserves a special mention. They are incredibly friendly and always greet you with a smile. I had a near miss experience once, and the staff members, Nic and Hyewon, went above and beyond to check in on my well being. It's clear that they genuinely care about providing the best experience for their members.

I highly recommend Anytime Fitness Bukit Timah Central. It's the perfect gym for those seeking convenience, well-maintained equipment, a cozy atmosphere, and a friendly staff who truly go the extra mile. Five stars without a doubt!

author: Benelma Burau-North
text:
I joined AF 6 months ago and the initial attraction was the flexibility you have to train anywhere and the range of equipment that is way and above my condo gym. I have been very impressed by the ethos and culture of the organisation as I have had a few challenges where I had to place membership on hold for medical reasons and there was no questions asked , just flexibility and an understanding that the company works around your needs and has waived fees etc. There is also not the presssure to commit to expensive PT like others gyms , you can take it or leave it and for example , just choose to have basic tracking such as the body composition analysis. I highly recommend this organisation to anyone wanting a quality and flexible experience for their gym membership.
Joelma Burau

author: Shakir Ahmed
text:
I was interested in a monthly membership. The fee was high but was still worth due to 24hr access. However, the registration fee is very high as well as a stupid key fob fee. I couldn't understand at this day and age, why the key fob fee isn't made to be paid as a deposit refundable upon membership termination and returning the key. It's such a stupid business decision.

What am I going to do with the key fob after I end membership? Hang it on my wall as a precious item, sell it or play with it? It's a complete waste of resources and disregard towards sustainability.

There are plenty of gyms around as good as AF or better in terms of equipment but with sensible pricing, so I think they're shooting themselves in the foot.

author: Yit Ying Kuan
text:
It's my first gym membership and I'm loving it ‚ù§Ô∏è  No comment on their gym equipment cos' I'm only there for the swimming pool and the studio space. The pool is always clean and empty during lunch and you'll get all the sun you want! The studio space is also more than enough for me to practice my ballet, just that it's sometimes a little dusty. Teehee.

Yoga classes are included in the monthly membership fee. For the lesson quality, it's definitely more than its worth. OH, i like how they drop reminders before classes tooüòÄ

As for the ladies bathroom, it's 2 in 1 with the toilet. Not very comfy but still works. The hairdryer is better than the one i have at home, so I'm  more than happy to workout there before work or during lunch every day.

Staffs are friendly and helpful, and its always nice to talk to them. All in all, love it and it made me stick to my not-so-intense workout plans. Yay!

18 Apr 2024: Due to some personal reasons, I won't be able to go to gym for a long period of time, so I wanted to cancel my membership. The staff suggested to freeze my account instead of cancelling it, as my case is within the clause for freezing the account (I didn't know about this option.) I'm glad that the staff is well versed with the t&c and gave me the most suitable option. Cheers!

author: Jacynda Teo
text:
While the AF Kovan branch boasts a larger layout compared to other North East outlets, the narrow rectangular side makes it quite inconvenient. It‚Äôs challenging to navigate the space, especially when people carrying weights have to maneuver through‚Äîeveryone else has to step aside, which can be quite frustrating.

Many of the seats on the machines were torn, and several of the bars were rusty. This level of neglect is concerning and reflects poorly on the overall maintenance of the facility.

What truly horrified me, however, was the condition of the facilities. After using their DIY soap and kitchen towel to clean my hands, I found them covered in rust! It‚Äôs incredibly off-putting and raises serious concerns about cleanliness and maintenance.

I hope the management addresses these issues soon, but based on my experience, I can‚Äôt recommend this branch at the moment.

author: Jacynda Teo
text:
I‚Äôm thrilled with my experience at the AF Upper Serangoon branch! The gym is incredibly cozy and feels relatively brand new, which was a big factor in my decision to sign up with AF. The modern and clean environment makes working out a pleasure.

One minor downside is that the toilet is located outside the gym. However, this actually contributes to a cleaner and more organized changing room area, which is a nice trade-off. The overall neatness of the facility is definitely a plus.

The layout of the machines is well-planned, making the workout space both functional and efficient. It‚Äôs clear that a lot of thought went into the design to ensure a great user experience.

Overall, I‚Äôm very satisfied with this location and highly recommend it to anyone looking for a top-notch gym experience!

author: Tim
text:
Asked for a free trial specifically to exercise with the equipments, and when I reached there I was suddenly told it was just a tour and not a trial. Made me waste time prepping the workout before and coming all the way down. Had to find another gym to do my workout that morning.

Granted it was a miscom, I was open to come back another day for a trial before signing up, but the saleperson that I spoke via text gave bad attitude and was not apologetic at all, and that it was me who didn't read the poster that he sent me for the trial timings. Like hello, I came mentioning for a trial explicitly, and you sidestepped it into just a tour instead. How can a new customer know what's the diff between a tour and trial if you don't even bother to explain, and say its ok to come down when I asked for a trial? And he still had the gall to say I could have just signed up on the spot, then can use the gym straightaway.

Very bad customer service.. Looking at the reviews here about how the management is rude to even their existing members, and how they don't bother to maintain the equipment, I am glad I had this encounter before I signed.

To the owner: if you value your revenue, keep tabs on your staff and make sure they treat people right. Its honestly amazing how your staff can turn a very ready prospective lead off to such an extent and lose a business. All the best
