author: ty pang
text:
Terrible experience with this gym! Think twice before you sign up. Their service is a huge letdown (especially Jasmine).

Here's the deal: They automatically renew your contract, no matter how long you joined for. But guess what? Canceling that renewal is a nightmare! I signed up for 6 months, thinking it'd be easy to end. But oh boy, was I wrong! When I tried to cancel, there were all these hidden rules. In the end, they forced me to pay for an extra month. And get this: They say you can cancel if you move far away. But guess what? There's no way to do it! I couldn't even end the renewal on time! Seriously, if I can't finish my 6-month membership in 6 months, why do they call it that?

I told them I wanted to cancel early, but they said I had to wait until the last month. But by then, I'd be long gone from Singapore. Can you believe it? They acted like they were doing me a favor by allowing a virtual cancellation. None of this cancellation stuff is in the contract, but their staff keeps insisting on it. It's just nonsense!

There are already so many bad reviews out there, and this Jasmine person is like a superstar on other apps, like RedBook. Just search her name and you'll see what I mean!

author: Godwin Koh
text:
Look no further if you are into a gym that is inclusive and not intimidating at all. So many friendly people coming from a wide range of background. From old to young. From experienced to the "newbie".

The gym is also quite big, with an open space that is frequently used to hold classes (If you are into this sort of perks).

Its also one of the few rare gym that offers an entire bathroom suite for us to shower instead of cubicles. It makes the whole place even more cosy.

If you are into the connection with the staff, fret not, look out for Elene! She gave a very well tailored explanation when i was signing up, very understanding to my situation as a student and was able to wait for my decision without being intrusive.

From what i can see,  the PTs are very engaging and they would often put in the extra effort to make sure their client pushes to their hardest.

All good times with minimal fuss.

author: Sihan Goi
text: Very good gym. It's new, it's clean, it's not packed, it's not huge but rather spacious, and it has pretty much all the equipment I need. 1 Hammer Strength small platform (good for deadlifts/snatches but probably not so much for split jerks), 1 Hammer Strength power rack, 1 Hammer Strength squat rack, 1 Movement First barbell (1 side makes a noise when you spin it, but works fine), 1 unmarked (Ziva?) barbell (it spins so all good), and the highlight for me is the 1 Eleiko WL bar. There are also Hammer Strength coloured bumpers from 5-25kg. No toilets here (only shower and changing rooms), and the lockers are a tad small for larger duffle bags, but other than that, no complaints!

author: Aaron Rozells
text:
Great gym with welcoming environment for both beginners and experts.

I struggled with fitness issues for some but I approached fitness trainer Maple Tan to help me on my journey. Truly dedicated to both coaching and inspiring, Maple took on the role of an amazing mentor in which not only did she coach with patience, she also gave me advice on changes I should make in terms of lifestyle and diet.

Maple is extremely willing to share her immense wealth of knowledge with her clients and never fails to wear a smile to add cheer and joy in order to make training as enjoyable as possible.

I truly recommend Maple to clients of any gender and I am extremely grateful of her training.

Here are the results I have managed to obtain with Maple in 10 sessions, which approximate to about 70 days of training:

Body fats decr. 4.1%
Visceral fat decr. 31cm2
Muscle incr. 1.5kg
Weight decr. 5.4kg

author: Eugene K
text:
I must say, this gym is not just spacious, but also well-equipped with a vast studio, a free weights area, and a machine area. You can find 6 squat racks, 2 cable machines, and 1 smith machine, which are all in excellent condition.

While the gym sees a manageable crowd during the morning and lunchtime, it can get a bit crowded during dinner time and night. However, it doesn't really affect the overall gym experience.

One thing that really stood out for me is the Evolt body analyzer, which has been immensely helpful in evaluating my body composition. It enables me and my physical trainer to keep a check on my body fat and muscle composition, leading to progress monitoring.

Speaking of my physical trainer, Risham, I must say he is exceptional. With his vast experience, he has been able to guide me in proper movements for both free weights and machines. Besides, I have learned many useful stretching techniques from him, which have helped me improve my flexibility.

What's more impressive is that Risham has also taught me additional exercise techniques such as sport massage and suspension training. He focuses on compound movements that stress multiple muscle groups and has helped me cover the whole body effectively.

In short, if you are looking for a gym with excellent equipment and an experienced physical trainer like Risham, this is the place to be.

The service here for membership is preposterous. The staff whatsapped me the rates, and when I went down physically they told me the rates and both were the same: it was 12 or 18 monthly and the rates were paid monthly, but if you pay in lump sum you will get 1 month free. However in the end, when I was about to confirm they told me only lump sum option available (in a take it or leave it manner) and no reply after I asked why the offer was different from the original conversations I had.
How can you offer different prices at different times at your whimsy and as a customer I just find the service to be terrible. Will not sign up with this gym and found a much better gym elsewhere. My guess is that they have enough capacity for members and don‚Äôt value new members hence the treatment.

author: regina deang
text:
I have been to four AF outlets, and this is the only one where I felt humiliated. One of their staff members kicked me out simply for forgetting my key fob, despite being a member of their gym. I understand that I *may* not be allowed to enter without my key fob, but can this outlet at least be compassionate and polite when speaking to members about this? I‚Äôm not expecting to be treated like royalty, just as a decent human being with emotions.

Other gym brands have more convenient ways of accessing the gym, like logging in through their phone app. Additionally, other AF gym outlets are more considerate when members forget their key fob (note: it's not about being non-compliant, but about being considerate). I tried to raise this concern with their management, but I think they‚Äôre tone-deaf on the issue. They cannot even do a proper customer service response. It‚Äôs not like we‚Äôre going there to rob them.

I‚Äôm tired of the "take it or leave it" mentality. It was very frustrating that I had to wait two months to transfer to another gym with better customer service. It was also disappointing that I paid for an additional two months at this gym, only to be treated as though I should be grateful just to be a member of their ‚Äúspecial gym‚Äù.

I‚Äôm glad I‚Äôm no longer a member. Best of luck to the current members or those who want to sign up.

author: Roger Thomas Tan
text: Gym is great! Equipments are new, free weights are new! Cosy but the members are few so you can just use whatever station you like - good for those who find it easier not to share or wait for stations! The bathroom is awesomely great too! Nicely fitted shower head! Their mirror outside the bathroom makes you look bigger than you really are - great for guys wanting to train and look big! The music they play are reggae, acid jazz and lounge! Really sensually classy! Unlike some other gyms which like to blast techno! They have tons of things like zero calories salad dressing, bbq sauce, jam! Plus even have details on getting affordable steamed chicken breast for healthy eating! So you see people running this gym is serious abt getting fit and trimming fats! Great job to the manager Eugene! Just nite that the toilet is outside at the back- you need to bring your token with you if you want to get back. Parking is at the back near the private estate. Or you can park at Upper Serangoon shopping Center and take a nice stroll over. Once again great job guys! I love this gym! Thanks for all the effort Manager Eugene! Guys you need to use this gym if you are in Kovan area! It‚Äôs simply great!

author: Kimberley Howarth
text: Really nice and well maintained gym. There is a large selection of machines, free weights, and cardio equipment. They also have a large studio. The biggest studio of all the branches so far, I believe. And they have a good selection of classes. I appreciate that the trainers/staff also leave you alone and let you do your own thing... and not follow you around trying to make conversation or try to talk or bully you into buying a package. I like that a lot. Even the person who attended to me when I came to enquire for membership (Yusri) was very relaxed and chill, and did not try to hard sell me or give me an hour long sales talk like so many other commercial fitness centres do. Thats was the main reason why I decided to sign up here. Only thing is the music is way too loud... I have trouble listening to my own music and surely it cant be good for your hearing to have the music turned up so loud. It's supposed to be a gym right, not a nightclub. The toilets and showers are pleasant and clean. One of the shower lights is not working. And the step to the washrooms are also quite a fall hazard. Why the step was built like this, who knows!

text:
Disappointing. After weeks of notifying staff that the airconditioning is off after midnight, making the conditions of those who train during those hours very unsatisfying, nothing has changed. Occasionally even see trainers come in at 7am and notice that the airconditioned has been turned off the whole time and just giggle. Not sure how difficult it is to keep the AC on after midnight or at least notify people that it will be kept off. So far just empty assurances. Not recommended at all for anyone planning to train after midnight, inconsistent and poorly managed. Staff will give you a hard time if you squat without shoes in the power rack, but not do anything about anyone who doesnt rerack their weight or use towels.

Never posted a review in my life, but clearly none of the friendly feedback given so far has led to any change, so here you go.

author: oikaru
text: It has been 2 months since I signed up to be a member. Initially, I was skeptical of the reviews as everyone have good things to say. I'm here to make a statement that - YES ANYTIME FITNESS PP IS THAT AMAZING!! from the cleanliness of the toilets to the service of the staff, it feels like a second home to me. One incident that particularly touched my heart was when I had a terrible day but two of the gym staff cheered me up and listened to me. I appreciate the kind gesture of them offering me chocolate too! That aside, the equipment is well maintained and even the gym-goers are kind and friendly. If you're thinking of signing up, PLEASE DO! The Gym Manager William is amazing as well and he bothers to remember which member signs up. Furthermore, AF PP isn't overcrowded with a ton of gym-goers so it feels peaceful and less suffocating gym-ing here :)

It is a base for a group of powerlifters. While I understand and respect that many treat this gym as their training base, it is ultimately a commercial gym that should be welcoming to all users. It‚Äôs very unpleasant when some powerlifters treat it like their personal gym,  hogging equipment and exhibiting rude and xenophobic behaviour towards others in the space. Communication and respect should be paramount to ensure that everyone can enjoy their workout without feeling unwelcome.

author: Matthew Tse
text:
I cannot say enough positive things about my personal trainer, Reece! He has truly transformed my gym experience and changed my lifestyle!

Reece's dedication and expertise have been instrumental in helping me reach my fitness goals. His tailored workouts and nutritional guidance have been spot-on, and I've seen remarkable progress since I started training with him.

What sets Reece apart, though, is how he's made the gym a better place for everyone. He's not just a trainer; he's a motivator and a source of positive energy. He creates an inclusive and welcoming environment, making sure everyone feels comfortable and encouraged, regardless of their fitness level.

His passion for fitness is contagious, and it's evident that he genuinely cares about his clients' well-being. Reece's support goes beyond the gym sessions; he's always available to answer questions, provide guidance, and offer that extra bit of motivation when you need it most.

As a personal trainer, he also works hard to improve himself. Ever since I started training with him, I witnessed how much I changed and he too, become better and stronger! Seeing how he trains himself, I am inspired to push further too!

If you're looking for a personal trainer who not only helps you achieve your fitness goals but also makes your gym experience enjoyable and inspiring, Reece is the one! I can't recommend him enough. Thank you, Reece, for making the gym a better place for all of us! üí™üèãÔ∏è‚Äç‚ôÇÔ∏èüëè

P.S. Although the gym is getting hotter and stuffier recently, and the management does not seem to care, Reece's dedication and positive energy definitely made up for it! Hopefully the management will review and fix the fans and aircon to make the gym an even better place for everyone! Thank you Reece for changing my lifestyle to a better, healthier one. Looking forward to more sessions with you! The 5 stars are all for Reece btw. üòä

author: Wong Wei Sen
text:
I‚Äôve been to many gyms before, but my experience at Anytime Fitness BTC has been by far the worst. The first thing that stands out is the staff ‚Äì instead of being approachable or helpful, they are constantly on their phones, eating at the counter, and ignoring members. It feels like they have no interest in assisting guests or maintaining any level of professionalism, which is incredibly frustrating when you‚Äôre paying for a membership.

The equipment situation is just as bad. Weights and machines are left scattered all over the place, with no effort to keep things organized or safe. Many machines look poorly maintained, and it gives the impression that management doesn‚Äôt care about upkeep at all. On top of that, the air-conditioning is broken, which turns the entire gym into a stuffy, smelly sauna. Instead of being motivating, the environment makes you want to leave as quickly as possible.

The cleanliness is another major issue. The toilets and changing areas are always dirty, with an unpleasant smell that lingers. For a gym that is supposed to promote health and fitness, the level of hygiene is shockingly low.

Overall, this branch feels completely neglected, both by its staff and management. Instead of being a place to focus on training and wellness, it is uncomfortable, unhygienic, and unprofessional. I would never recommend Anytime Fitness BTC to anyone looking for a decent gym experience ‚Äì it‚Äôs disappointing on every single level.

author: tan mingkai
text:
Largest AF i've been to, had alot of great equipment,

+ abundance of squat racks, like 6 or 8 of them

+/- 5 Deadlift platforms are also more than most but the platforms are configured abit awkwardly where theres one in the middle and on either sides there are 2 that are inches away from each other, i'd say they should rotate them 90 degrees and have them in a row spaced farther apart but I dont know enough about owning a gym to make that recommendation.

+ Other than the typical selection of machines that all AFs have they also had some Panatta equipment so if you like variety they're good.

+/- Pretty serious gym despite all the controversy when it first opened, but with all serious gyms, you get your intimidating atmosphere and yelling when PRs are hit so do be emotionally and mentally prepared.

+/- Changing room/ toilet is relatively large, can get a bit untidy what with all the various lifting belts and shoes people bring with them, large mirrors for your selfies.

Went on a Friday evening, moderate attendance, some people trying their best to do a hyrox challenge.

author: Janie S.B Tan
text:
Everyone would have read about how big and spacious and new the gym is so I wouldn't repeat the same comments again. I would like to comment on the customer service aspect of it and I must say as of now, I'm blown away by it, be it the instructors or administrators.

I used to be a gym member for many years before California fitness closed down. After ten years of not being in the gym, signing up for one somehow felt a bit scary for me, but from sign-up to registering for classes to attending classes, it has been a really pleasant experience for me. Sign-up was easy and relaxing because the staff was really friendly (Alex and William); Class registration is really quick using the app and the instructors, though having to teach very very small classes because afterall this is a new gym, are very friendly, full of energy and enthusiastic nonetheless.

When the COVID hit, I was worried about my gym membership because the gym is close to my workplace but very far from my home, but the team reacted very fast and William the club manager suspended my membership. I am very grateful and surprised by their understanding because in my former gym, when I had to be overseas for a few months and I asked for a suspension, it was a real struggle to get it approved.

And during this COVID period, I get messages from the gym sometimes on various things like free online workout classes by their instructors, free temporary access to Les milles classes, or just simply a hi and check on my well-being.

And though it is not directly affecting me per se, I love the fact that they are still paying their staff even though I know most gyms have asked their staff to go on unpaid leave due to the COVID situation. I always believe that happy employees means happy customers. I really have to give them my thumbs and toes up for this.

Their passion to provide world class service and utmost care for their gym members and staff really makes me proud to be part of the AF Pasir Panjang family.

Good job AF PP.

There is this middle aged Chinese gentleman with a beard(not that I have any issues with his age) wearing singlet and spandex that trains around this timing as well for 3-4 hours. He would pace around the gym with his headphones on and grunt excessively loud as well as obnoxiously slam the weights especially on the lat pulldown machine causing a distraction to other gym members and even frightening some to the point where they feel uncomfortable to train near him and would physically move to the other side of the gym. I understand if he grunts when the weight is heavy but he does it even when the weight is relatively light. He would also pace around the gym and stare at other members giving off a very intimidating vibe. I am astounded that the staff ignores his lack of gym etiquette and I can say this would be a reason for me to not return to the gym. I really hope the staff would give him a verbal warning because I myself have seen other members especially females feel really intimidated by him and I am sure they have lodged a complaint as well. Hope to see some follow up on this because I really like this outlet!

author: James Ong
text:
Title: A Top-Notch Fitness Experience at Anytime Fitness Gym

Rating: ‚òÖ‚òÖ‚òÖ‚òÖ‚òÖ

I have been a member at Anytime Fitness gym for over a year now, and I can confidently say that it has been an exceptional fitness experience. This gym has truly exceeded my expectations in terms of its facilities, services, and overall atmosphere.

First and foremost, the gym's 24/7 access is a game-changer. It allows me to work out whenever it suits my schedule, whether it's early in the morning, late at night, or even during holidays. This flexibility has been a massive advantage, especially for someone with a busy lifestyle like mine.

The facilities at Anytime Fitness are top-notch. The gym is spacious, well-maintained, and equipped with a wide range of state-of-the-art exercise machines, weights, and cardio equipment. The cleanliness and organization of the entire facility are remarkable, ensuring a comfortable and hygienic workout environment.

What sets Anytime Fitness apart from other gyms is its friendly and knowledgeable staff. The trainers are approachable, professional, and always ready to assist with any questions or concerns. They offer personalized guidance and create customized workout plans to help members achieve their fitness goals effectively and safely.

Another aspect that I appreciate about Anytime Fitness is the diverse range of group classes they offer. From yoga and Zumba to HIIT and cycling, there is something for everyone. These classes are led by experienced instructors who offer motivation and challenge members to push their limits while ensuring proper form and technique.

The gym's focus on member safety and security is also commendable. The facility is equipped with surveillance cameras, emergency buttons, and a secure access system, making me feel safe during my late-night workouts. Additionally, the gym strictly follows COVID-19 safety protocols, providing hand sanitizers, enforcing social distancing, and regularly sanitizing equipment.

Anytime Fitness also offers a convenient mobile app that allows members to track their workouts, join challenges, and access workout routines. This technology integration is a great addition to the overall gym experience, making it easier to stay motivated and on track with fitness goals.

Lastly, the membership fees at Anytime Fitness are reasonable, especially considering the quality of facilities and services provided. They also offer various membership options, including month-to-month plans, family plans, and corporate discounts, catering to a diverse range of individuals.

Overall, Anytime Fitness gym has proven to be a fantastic choice for anyone looking for a well-rounded fitness experience. With its 24/7 access, top-notch facilities, knowledgeable staff, and commitment to member safety, it has become my go-to gym. I highly recommend Anytime Fitness to anyone seeking a gym that prioritizes convenience, quality, and a supportive fitness community.

author: Ryan Chan
text:
Experienced a group of rude gym users demanding their use of equipment during peak hours and would have appreciated if staffs were more proactive on the ground, especially during peak hours, and recovery service after the incident was informed to one of the staff. This review is posted since I've yet to receive any updates from the staff after 5 days.

The incident happen on 30/4/24 between 7.25pm to 7.30pm at the caged rack located near to the Plated Leg Press. As the bench within the rack was empty with no sign of "booking" of the equipment such as placing of towel or phone on the bench, I went ahead to use it and completed 2 warm-up sets with no interference. 2 guys came to me after saying that they were using the bench. I politely told them that it was empty when I came to use and that there were no signs of anyone "booking" it and if they could use another empty bench that were located beside the Plated Chest Press machine. One of the guys rudely replied "No" and continued to give unreasonable reasoning as to how the bench was theirs. I did not want to cause a scene as I was clearly communicating with someone who isn't rationale and clearly egoistic. I offered to clean the equipment since I've used it but they rejected and laughed it off.

This incident was later communicated to a short Malay female staff and I requested her to investigate in this matter and get back to me regarding the resolution to such behavior within the facility and left my contact details with her. Given the benefit of doubt that the next day was Labour Day, I was expecting a response the day after. It has been 5 days since thus I decided to write this review with regards to both the standards of discipline within the gym as well as the proactiveness of the staff in this situation. I hope this group of individuals are not terrorizing other gym users with their unreasonable gym ethics else I would foresee more poor reviews in the future given the fact that this gym, in terms of equipment and staff politeness, are well above average.

For users who have seen this review and wonder if there's anything that can be done during such incident of unreasonable demands, I would highly suggest you to approach the gym staff immediately to sound it off.

text:
I've been an active member of Anytime Fitness for many years since joining it's first branch at Ace The place CC. Had also subsequently visited many other branches to find a branch of my expectations.

When I saw that the Sembawang branch was starting, it also prompted me to try it out and since then, I've stuck to it for years and counting.

One of the main reasons for my decision are because of the friendly atmosphere I got when in the gym. The management and all their staff members are so friendly and very helpful to everyone; and I believe this is the reason why it's such a friendly and family oriented branch.  And this friendly approach rubs on to everyone in the gym thus most members do get to know each other very fast. Have made many friends of similar interest here.

The equipments for all muscle groups are sufficiently available and most importantly is that they are well maintained and any faulty parts are replaced very quickly. There are also alot of classes in the gym to choose from, regardless whether you're a beginner or an advanced gym goer.

Kudos to the Sembawang Anytime Fitness management and staff of the  for being able to create such a great  ambiance to workout in.

Keep it up guys! üí™

author: Alex D
text:
I won‚Äôt dwell on the negative reviews about the moldy toilets since that‚Äôs been covered enough already.

As a long-time member visiting this branch for the first time, I actually had to stop my workout halfway through and head to another branch just to finish it. The way this gym is set up is really strange compared to others.

Like many have said, the second floor is empty, and all the foot traffic is on the first floor. Yet the only water dispenser is on the second floor.

There are three power racks but only one bench available.

In the dumbbell area, there‚Äôs only one adjustable bench, while the rest are flat benches, which would‚Äôve made more sense in the power rack area.

Lastly, the cable pulley section doesn‚Äôt even have a rope handle. There are four pulley machines, but the most commonly used attachments are missing. The other AF branches have plenty of them.

It‚Äôs as if the gym manager doesn‚Äôt even work out and has no clue how things should function.

author: Mia PGB
text:
My husband and I were gaining weight and we had no excuse. It was the health issues we were experiencing that prompted us to go on a fitness plan. Anytime Fitness Sembawang and their personal trainer Nina helped us a lot in getting the results we wanted.

The gym is well equipped and ventilated. All the staff, from the managers, trainers and maintenance are super friendly, approachable, and very supportive from day one. The gym itself and the equipment are really clean, which we greatly appreciated. I was never uncomfortable whenever I was there. The gym being a stone's throw away from our work place was also a plus.

Nina is an amazing trainer. I am grateful for her patience, support and encouragement. She has set a regime for us to follow that worked very well. We were able to get to our fitness goals with hard work, dedication and determination not only by me and my husband but with Nina as well. She was with us althroughout and has been a huge part of us being healthy. We only have fond memories of you, Nina!

The benefit of being with Anytime Fitness is that you can use any of their gyms as long as you have your fob with you. We lived in Ang Mo Kio and it was never troublesome for us to visit AF's other branches during our off days and away from Sembawang. This is applicable internationally, too.

Unfortunately, we had to say goodbye to this amazing gym because we migrated to Australia in January this year. Although our journey with  Anytime Fitness Sembawang was short, it was definitely a fruitful and enjoyable experience. We are planning to sign up with AF near our place soon.

Thank you for the wonderful experience, AF Sembawang! We are missing this awesome gym a lot! üí™

Regards to everyone!

Mia & August

author: Jian Yang Lee
text:
I joined this branch since their opening in December 2023. Giving my first google review to AF JTC, cheers! It's one of the best gyms in the west (Honorable mentions: AF D'Arena, AF Clementi, AF Jurong Point, and AF Bukit Batok CSC). West side, best side!

Reasons why you should join AF JTC:

1. **Powerlifter-friendly gym**: They have plenty of squat racks and deadlift platforms. So, powerlifters, y'all must be orgasm right now.

2. **Spacious environment**: With a 5,000 sq ft gym, you won't feel like you're clubbing when working out during peak hours. Some AF outlets are too small, making me feel like I was clubbing at Marquee or Zouk.

3. **Easy access**: It's just a 5-minute walk from Jurong East MRT and is sheltered. Furthermore, it is located opposite the bus interchange.

Hopefully, they will add some extra machine in the future!

author: Daryl Wang
text:
I recently joined Anytime Fitness Chai Chee, and I must say, it has been an amazing experience! From the moment my colleague and I stepped into the gym, we were warmly welcomed by the team, and the overall vibe was fantastic.

A special shoutout to Koji, the manager, who played a huge role in our decision to sign up immediately. His professionalism, friendliness, and genuine enthusiasm for fitness made us feel confident that we were making the right choice. He took the time to understand our goals, walked us through the facilities, and ensured that we felt comfortable and excited to begin our fitness journey.

The gym itself is well-equipped, clean, and has a great environment that makes working out enjoyable. Whether you're a beginner or an experienced gym-goer, this place has everything you need.

I highly recommend Anytime Fitness Chai Chee to anyone looking for a welcoming and supportive gym community. And if you‚Äôre lucky enough to meet Koji, you‚Äôll see why this branch stands out!

text: I joined Anytime Fitness a couple of months ago to pursue a healthier lifestyle, and despite having a gym in my apartment, I chose to continue my fitness journey here because of the amazing atmosphere. author: Jameson Tan
text:
The gym offers a welcoming atmosphere, with friendly and approachable staff who make every visit enjoyable. They go the extra mile by offering a free body scan every three months, helping members track their progress and stay motivated. Occasionally, they even give out complimentary parking coupons, adding a nice touch of convenience for their members. For added comfort, they provide free towels for members to use during their workouts. The equipment is always well-maintained, ensuring a safe and effective workout environment. The community is equally supportive, with members being friendly and always willing to share tips and advice, making it a great place to grow and achieve your fitness goals.

Highly recommended!

author: Romee TuTu
text:
While registration is easy, cancelling the membership is a nightmare. They require members to send an email after the expiry date, which is unnecessarily troublesome. If they don‚Äôt receive the email (or claim not to), you‚Äôre automatically charged for another month‚Äî$99, no less! They also have a ridiculous 30-day notice period for cancellations. Why make it so hard for members to leave?

For a gym charging this much, the service should at least be decent. Instead, the staff are unprofessional, as seen in other Google reviews where someone was body-shamed. This is unacceptable. If I wanted to donate money, I‚Äôd give it to charity, not to a gym that lacks basic accountability.

Avoid this place unless you enjoy unnecessary fees and poor service.

author: nic nic
text:
Unprofessional Conduct and Racial Harassment by Staff ‚Äî Extremely Disappointing.

I am appalled and deeply disturbed by my recent experiences at AFNQW.
On multiple occasions during my visits, a staff member named Fiqah made racist and hateful comments toward her colleagues.
She openly joked and made derogatory remarks about specific races and cultures ‚Äî and these comments were loud enough for members and guests to hear.

In addition to the blatant racism, her overall attitude at the front desk was unprofessional and hostile.
While other staff consistently greeted guests with "Hi! Welcome!" upon entry and "Bye! Have a nice day!" when leaving, Fiqah would sit at the desk, glued to her phone, shaking her leg, and barely acknowledging anyone. Her nonchalant and dismissive demeanor created an unwelcoming and uncomfortable environment.

It is completely unacceptable to see this level of poor hospitality and blatant misconduct at an AF location, especially one operating under Reformd.
A business that allows staff to behave this way ‚Äî both through racism and general rudeness ‚Äî is not only violating basic ethical standards but also exposing itself to serious legal and reputational risks.
No one should have to tolerate racism or hostility, especially in a shared, confined space like a gym.

Until corrective action is taken, I cannot recommend this gym to anyone who values respect, inclusivity, and professionalism.

author: Emerick Mitchell Donovan
text:
STAY AWAY! For your own good.
This has been, hands down, the worst customer service experience I‚Äôve ever encountered. I‚Äôm writing this so others can make an informed decision before signing up.

I‚Äôve been a loyal member of Anytime Fitness since 2018. On 7 April 2025, I underwent an emergency stomach operation. I was placed on Hospitalisation Leave until 2 May, and subsequently given light duty until 29 May‚Äîmeaning no strenuous activity or exercise was allowed during this recovery period, as per medical advice.

On 11 April, I reached out to the Admiralty Anytime Fitness outlet via text with the medical memo, requesting a freeze on my account until 29 May. I also asked for the April payment (which I had already made but couldn‚Äôt use) to be offset in my June bill. A simple, reasonable request‚Äîone that other gyms I‚Äôm a member of had no issue accommodating with empathy and zero hassle.

What followed was a mess. They got back to me days later saying they'd waive 24 days of April and charge me $11.53 instead of $85 for May. The math didn‚Äôt add up, so I broke it down for them clearly (screenshots available). That‚Äôs when the excuses started. Suddenly, I was told a 30-day advance notice was required to freeze memberships. How exactly does one give 30 days' notice for an emergency surgery?

It got worse. I was then told that ‚Äúlight duty‚Äù meant I could do ‚Äúlight workouts.‚Äù Let that sink in; a fitness outlet trying to interpret a medical memo in their favor. I explained it simply meant I could return to office to do desk work.

After further follow-up, they came back and said they‚Äôd now only waive the month of May.
I asked‚Äîagain‚Äîif they could simply offset April‚Äôs payment in my June bill, as I couldn't use the gym while recovering from surgery. I wasn‚Äôt asking for a refund. Just a deferment/offset. They refused.

They began asking if this injury/operation was caused by the gym. How in the WORLD is that relevant?

They also refused to let me speak to management or send me the contract terms when I requested them‚Äîtwice. Instead, I was told:
‚ÄúUnder contract T&Cs, members have to pay regardless of whether they come or not.‚Äù

As if that wasn‚Äôt dismissive enough, they said ‚Äú
If today you lost your phone and you can't use your telco services anymore for 2 weeks, you do not go to your telco and tell them to refund you the $ since u do not have your phone to use their services right..‚Äù

Yes, that was the example and comparison given.

Frankly, I‚Äôm shocked. After seven years of loyalty, this is the level of treatment towards a paying customer. The experience has been nothing short of appalling, and I would urge anyone considering a membership at this outlet to think twice.

author: K W
text:
We were so lucky to meet Tessa during our trial at AF Thomson. She trains a young senior in the family. She has been impressive from the first day - she gave a personalised overview of her training plan according to the needs and preferences of the student, took time to learn the student's schedule and home training facilities so that the student can continue training elsewhere on other days, and took videos and gave updates after each training session so that the student can keep track of her own progress.

Its not common to find someone as responsible, responsive, firm yet encouraging like Tessa.  She's a quiet personality but her actions inspire confidence.  She adapts her training well to the student.  Honestly, would recommend her wholeheartedly.

The AF facilities are also clean and bright.  The PT package permits payment in tranches, and so that also gives assurance.

text:
I‚Äôve been a member of this gym since it first opened, and honestly, it‚Äôs been getting worse over time. There are no wet wipes available, the towels are dirty and smelly, and most of the spray containers aren‚Äôt working properly or are empty. It‚Äôs unclear what the staff is doing,  it seems like they‚Äôre more focused on gathering 5-star reviews  rather than actually improving the gym‚Äôs facilities.

Reading all the glowing reviews here honestly feels misleading. There‚Äôs been no noticeable improvement since the gym opened. I really hope the staff and management are more transparent about the reviews. It feels like they‚Äôre deceiving people into thinking the gym is efficient and well-run, when in reality, the focus seems to be on collecting ratings rather than addressing the issues that matters!

The management should really take a closer look at the reviews here. and should improve the facility.

author: Zhou Qing
text:
Disappointed with my recent experience at this Anytime Fitness outlet. During my visit, I encountered aggressive hard selling from the personal trainers, who dismissed my prior training experience without properly understanding or assessing my current workout routine. Instead, they pushed for an expensive training package costing over $3,000, which felt more like a sales tactic than genuine guidance.

Additionally, I was asked to make a downpayment equivalent to three months of membership fees, on top of the standard joining fee and key fob cost. I was told this was a new policy, yet other members who signed up over a year ago were not required to make such a large upfront payment and were allowed to pay monthly instead. This inconsistency in policy and lack of transparency is frustrating and left me feeling misled.

I hope the management takes this feedback seriously to ensure a more respectful, transparent and consistent approach moving forward.

author: Maryy Tan
text:
Disclosure: l am a current member of AF BTC and am sharing my personal experience. I am not affiliated with the gym owner or staff. Recent LL post is questionable (as gf of staff J). This gym USED to be my favourite, but unfortunately, things have taken a downturn in recent months. The overall experience has become less enjoyable, primarily due to changes in staff behaviour and management response.
To the management and owner: This feedback is meant to be constructive. Members like myself have provided feedback in the past, but responses often feel generic and unaddressed. Simply directing members to a phone number without real action leaves concerns unresolved.
Here are some of the key issues observed:
1. Member Experience & Capacity: Happy existing members are your best advocates. Smiling ear to ear when signing up new customers is total contrast to sulky cold attitude when help requested by existing customers. Recently, the gym feels overcrowded and noisy, which impacts the workout environment. This has been mentioned in earlier reviews and remains a concern.
2. Cleanliness & Facilities: Toiletries used to be regularly replenished, and hygiene standards were high. Lately, maintenance appears inconsistent. The shower area now has temporary plastic racks on the floor, which adds clutter and feels unhygienic.
3. Noise Levels & Staff Conduct: Music volume is already high, but it is sometimes overpowered by loud conversations at the reception area (staff consistently socialising loudly amongst themselves beyond lunch hours). This detracts from the workout atmosphere.
4. Hygiene Measures: The removal of wet wipe stands has caused inconvenience. Using spray bottles and towels that may not be sanitized adequately raises hygiene concerns. Requests for wipes are often met with a standard ‚Äúout of stock‚Äù dismissive response by Jamie.
5. Equipment Accessibility: Some equipment appears to be stored in restricted-access room. It can be frustrating for members when staff do not readily assist in locating these items. Had a recent bad experience with staff Carmen - unwillingness to help shows in her sulky face.
Lastly, I hope this feedback is taken seriously by the management. The decline in service standards may eventually lead members to seek alternatives. Maintaining a positive, professional environment is key to retaining loyal members.

Finally moved with Kirtan my Personal Trainer from December 2022 to a new cleaner and better equipped Gym in Anytime Fitness MacPherson Mall.

Most importantly, Kirtan my PT is wonderful‚Ä¶patiently working with me‚Ä¶. Post super sedentary lifestyle, sarcopaenic, flat-footed and imbalanced. We have worked through post cardiac surgery, fractured ankle and now I am mostly pain free and working towards building muscle, strength and functionality.  Am now at my ideal body weight and soon I will be able to achieve some bucket lists items like wall climbing ‚Ä¶. author: Jerry Shi
text:
I‚Äôm honestly shocked by how bad this gym is. First of all, the place smells awful ‚Äî like sweat and mold that‚Äôs never been cleaned. It hits you the second you walk in and makes the whole workout experience miserable. But even worse than the smell is the attitude of the staff. They are incredibly rude, dismissive, and clearly have no interest in helping anyone, especially beginners. If you‚Äôre new or just trying to get started on your fitness journey, don‚Äôt expect any support here. Instead of offering guidance or encouragement, they look down on you like you don‚Äôt belong.

To make things even more frustrating, they refused to honor the free trial that they advertise. When we asked about it, the staff brushed us off with a bad attitude and told us it wasn‚Äôt available ‚Äî no explanation, no apology, just straight-up discrimination. It felt like they were picking and choosing who they allowed to join, and that‚Äôs completely unacceptable.

This gym is unprofessional, unfriendly, and feels like a toxic environment. I would never recommend it to anyone ‚Äî especially not to beginners or people just trying to get healthier. Save your money and your time. There are plenty of gyms that actually care about their members ‚Äî this is not one of them.

This gym provides a very poor experience overall. The facility smells bad, the staff are rude and unwelcoming‚Äîespecially toward beginners‚Äîand they refused to honor the advertised free trial. Their behavior felt discriminatory and unprofessional, making the gym an uninviting and toxic environment. This is not a place that supports new members or encourages a positive fitness journey.

text:
Worst AF in Singapore I have ever been to. Staffs are unfriendly, not helpful and don‚Äôt look very healthy and fit ( I would never hire them to coach me ). Equipments are old and rusty.
I was 32 weeks pregnant and tried to hit the gym whenever I feel like I can. My mind is all over the place and my feet were swelling. In addition, I planned to just training my core with very light dumbbells at the stretching area that day. Therefore the last thing I want to do is training in my small, tight pair of converse shoes. It was fine with staffs at other AF because I mostly just stretch and exercise with yoga mat at the designated areas and only use light dumbbells for 1 exercises. The staff approached me and ask me to leave if I don‚Äôt have any cover shoes. What a horrible experience when you are trying to exercise while being pregnant! I didn‚Äôt let that ruins my exercise routine. I just go downstairs and buy me an another comfortable and casual pair of cover shoes and finished my exercises. I was too tired of my pregnancy to deal with the service yet.
In summary , I don‚Äôt think I will be back or purchase any services there any rime soon since there are a lot of choices around that areas. Serangoon garden, or upper Serangoon or Lorong Chuan.
Why putting myself in a dark cold, old and rusty, unfriendly and not supportive environment especially when I am a pregnant woman in my last trimester.

text:
The resplendent realm of fitness at Anytime Fitness City Square Mall boasts an unparalleled symphony of modernity and function. Upon entering, one is ensconced in an ambience of sophistication, where the luminous sheen of polished machinery dances in harmony with the serenity of the surroundings.

The gym's pi√®ce de r√©sistance undoubtedly lies in its cavalcade of new-fangled machines. Each apparatus, an epitome of cutting-edge innovation, beckons with its beguiling allure and ergonomic design, promising an odyssey towards physical prowess. These marvels of engineering, bedecked in sleek contours and adorned with polished finishes, stand as veritable monuments to the fusion of aesthetics and utility.

Moreover, the gym's ambiance exudes an ineffable charm. The air, redolent with the invigorating scent of determination, resonates with the rhythmic symphony of clinking weights and the hushed determination of the earnest patrons. This amalgamation of vibrant energy and tranquil repose creates an oasis of motivation, where each visit becomes an exquisite sojourn towards personal zenith.

In sum, Anytime Fitness City Square Mall is an empyrean haven for fitness enthusiasts, a pantheon where the opulence of contemporary machinery meets the soothing embrace of an inviting atmosphere, ensuring an unparalleled journey towards fitness fruition.

author: Filtered Fork Guide
text:
A disappointing decline in cleanliness and hygiene.

I have been a long-time member of this gym, and it's disheartening to witness its decline in cleanliness and hygiene standards since the pandemic. The once exceptional facility has become a shadow of its former self.

The state of the shower-rooms is appalling. Despite numerous posters reminding gym members not to urinate in these areas, the lingering smell of urine persists. It's both unpleasant and completely contrary to a sanitary environment that one expects from a reputable gym.

The gym's poor air-flow circulation contributes to an overwhelming stench of sweat throughout the premises.

Signing off,
Your local reviewer.

author: Grace Lim
text:
I'm trying to survey prices and packages for gyms in the area. Got contacted by the gym and they have been very shady about their prices. Will not reveal to me the exact price and packages either (only mentioned range $90-150) and kept pushing me to drop by to find out the prices. The worst kind of sales tactic. Especially during the pandemic point, they don't allow trials which is fair enough. Then what's the point you're increasing number of people in the gym by asking people to drop by? Don't allow gyms to do this to customers. Businesses should be transparent. Stop using MLM tactics.

Edit: Pricing policy is also not disclosed to me since you've brought it up. I don't have any interest in supporting shady tactics in business practices. My review is a warning to other potential people like me just trying to make good concious consumer decisions. Declining the invite to tour the gym as it's time-wasting if your prices itself are not favorable. Also read that there are no lockers or showers so I can't understand the crazy high price either.

author: Vanessa Tay
text:
The team at AF Cecil street are not helpful and are not there to help customers. As I consented to having my monthly payments be paid by Grab and due to technical issues by Grab that was of no fault of mine i.e. i fulfilled all the terms and conditions per the acknowledgement in the agreement, i wrote into AF Cecil street if they would consider waiving the late fee for this one time because it really was not anything on my part.

Without hesitation they redirect me to their payment platform EzPay to "help with my issue". I was to be redirected back to AF Cecil street as EzPay had mentioned that they were just "working on behalf of the merchant and any of the changes above should be conveyed to us by the merchant and would ultimately have an effect on how your direct debits are processed." which meant that AF Cecil street had every position and right to show good customer service to provide a one-time waiver.

However, they were so eager to earn from my late fee that they just responded with "Hi Vanessa, we understand your frustration. As much as we want to assist you on this matter. We are unable to do it." What kind of service is this? A gym that does not care for its patrons one bit, all it wishes to do is earn money. Not even bothering to consider the circumstances and provide some concession.

author: Tony Z
text:
I was ‚Äúautomatically transferred‚Äù to Tiong Bahru Anytime fitness, despite I still went to Paya Lebar one. It was transferred without my consent or without me knowing. Ever since transferred to TBR gym, it no longer sent me notification about gym payments. While I knew I didn‚Äôt opt-in for ‚Äúauto-renewal‚Äù of contract, I thought my contract would be terminated by Oct, or before Oct. i just found out that a deduction of gym membership from my bank transaction on 2 Nov. As I called the gym staff, she mentioned the auto-renewal would be automatically chosen from the gym transfer.
So basically, anytime fitness can do gym transfer & help customers choose auto-renewal of contracts without informing customers. And she said it was done automatically by the system. If I chose to terminate the contract, I need to give 30-day notice period.
Yesterday I made the call, she said she was alone in the gym, it was understaffed, and would give me response by last night. However, it did not. WhatsApp messages were just blue ticked without replies.
When I tried to call the gym to resolve the issue today, the gym has yet picked up the call.
From these incidents, definitely a poor service rating. It is not customer centric at all.
Maybe my last resort would be turn to lodging a business complaint or report for the unauthorized transactions. If anyone has any suggestions, thank you in advance.

author: E L
text:
If possible, do consider signing up with other outlet. Personally we are quite displease with the customer journey. Presale is awesome until you have sign up with them.

The mentioned opening date was at Sep 2021 but it have since been delayed till no tomorrow (end Oct 2021 as we are speaking.) What i mean is that if there is a delay its fine but i strongly feel that its the outlet responsibility to provide prompt notice to the newly signed up members. Instead you can see more effort are being put in to acquire new members.

They have also directed us to their social page for any updates and all i can see is the countdown to end of sale rather that the status update.

author: Leonard Chan
text:
I've signed up for 10 personal training sessions with PT Alan. Alan has been extremely enthusiastic and encouraging, and I feel like he truly does care for me and my goals. Alan is also very knowledgeable about the different muscle groups and guides and ensures that I am working out and activating the correct muscle groups. Alan also regularly checks in with me to remind me of my goals, progress and nutrition needs in between sessions. With his dedication to the health of his clients, I strongly encourage a PT package with Alan.

Update review: Originally 5 stars due to service rendered by PT Alan (he's the only saving grace for this gym). I wrote into their business WhatsApp number asking for a freeze in membership as I just had a circumcision procedure done. While the doctor gave me an MC for 7 days to allow me to rest at home from work, I was given a info sheet that states that I'm not supposed to do anything strenuous for at least 4 weeks after the procedure. However, management has declined my request for freezing my membership as they only see the 7 days of MC and do not consider the fact that all surgical procedures require more rest than the typical hospitalisation leave or medical leave given by doctors. It's akin to me receiving 21 days of hospitalisation leave after fracturing of my arm, then saying, oh because you only have 21 days so I will only give you 21 days of frozen membership - expecting a user to be able to utilise the gym after 21 days. It is easy to do a quick google to verify that any man who undergoes circumcision requires at least 4 weeks of rest. I'm extremely disappointed and appalled at such service. This encounter truly took the cake of all the disappointments that I've not voiced since the pre-sales period. I would rather pay a higher amount per month at another gym with more understanding and empathetic management. I wouldn't recommend signing up to this branch as it seems they do not have a case by case assessment of potential issues customers may face. Truly a disappointment.

author: Winston Jun
text:
What can i say, Anytime Fitness Pasir Panjang has everything that you want in a local gym. First off, the equipment are well mantained and clean and in these times of Covid, you see disinfectant sprays and wipes at almost every machine! No joke, its like every corner you turn, you would see 2 or 3 bottles. On top of that the space and equipment available is in ABUNDANCE i tell you, and to add on to that, they recently added even more equipement! You would find everything you need here.
The toilets, so clean and well mantained! They have a white colour scheme that is in no danger of getting stained or dirty despite it being a gym. This is thier commitment to hygiene and cleanliness. You have adequate number of shower rooms and changing rooms. They even have an aircon inside the toilet to keep you cool after your hot shower!

But the greatest thing for me, is the friendliness and warmth of the staff. They greet you so warmly like family at the door. So much so that if you walked in drenched from the rain, their hospitatlity would keep you warm. But please be advised to change out of your wet clothes. Among all the Anytime Fitness outlets i have been to, this one give me the most welcoming experience. There was once their club manger , William changed the weights for me on the bench press as he was worried that i was using different kind of weight plates, what a guy!

All in all, if you are looking for a place to start off your fitness journey, look no futher than Anytime Fitness Pasir Panjang! You won't regret it.

author: Erna Hanis
text:
I recently signed up for a gym membership at Anytime Fitness Sunway Bigbox and have had an outstanding experience, largely thanks to Coach Azry. From the moment I met him, his friendly demeanor and genuine interest in my fitness goals were evident. He took the time to understand what I wanted to achieve and explained the available packages without being pushy.

After a week of consideration, I decided to commit to training sessions with him, and it has been a fantastic decision. I‚Äôm now 14 sessions in, and Coach Azry has been incredibly patient and supportive throughout. His guidance extends beyond our sessions; even when I‚Äôm out of town, he provides me with exercise routines to follow, ensuring I stay on track with my goals.

What‚Äôs been particularly impressive is his holistic approach to fitness. Coach Azry has also offered valuable advice on nutrition, helping me understand how to fuel my body effectively to support my workouts and overall health. Additionally, he emphasizes the importance of adequate sleep and the impact it has on my fitness and recovery. While I‚Äôm still working on improving my sleep habits, I now understand why his emphasis on sleep is so crucial.

Coach Azry‚Äôs dedication and personalized approach have made a huge difference in my fitness journey. I highly recommend him to anyone looking for a knowledgeable and motivational trainer. Thanks to him, I feel more confident and motivated than ever!

Overall, Anytime Fitness Sembawang provides a convivial and safe space for both seasoned and amateur gym-goers, there is really little judgement which is very important for anyone to start or maintain a good exercising habit. The staff members are all very welcoming and always present to provide help and guidance. More importantly, they always keep the gym clean and tidy, please keep up with the awesome work!

author: Sihan Goi
text:
Came here on a tuesday morning and it was relatively quiet. This was the first AF I visited at the start of COVID-19, but I didn't join it then as the equipment wasn't what I expected, i.e. bumper plates and platforms. They recently got bumper plates and a platform (I think as part of their "glow up") so I visited it. The gym is rather small, but has quite a lot of equipment over 2 floors. Pretty much everything I need for a good strength workout. Free weights wise, there's 1 Hammer Strength full power rack with attached platform, another half rack, 2 sets of HS bumper plates from 10-25kg, except 20kg which has 3 sets, many other black rubberised plates, and 3 F1 recreation barbells that spin, but aren't as "tight" as the spin bars at other AF that use Eleiko/Ziva/HS/unbranded bars. It's 99% there though, but you will feel a bit of "give" when loading the HS bumper plates. Minor complaint. Another issue is that the ceilings aren't very high, so the pull up bars at the top of the racks are pretty much unusable as your head will likely hit the ceiling if you try doing pullups there. There are also various cable machines and cardio equipment

Upstairs, there are dumbbells up to 50kg, fixed bars, plate loaded machines, a warmup place with bands, kettlebells, a plyo-box, medicine balls, foam rollers, yoga blocks, and other assorted stuff. Strangely, there's a small glass room with a platform, half rack, barbells and plates, but it was for "Authorised personnel only". This is the first AF I've been to that has this, I guess it's anytime but not anywhere.

There are bathroom facilities on both floors, and the downstairs one looks nice and very well maintained for an AF. There's 1 staff on duty during the time I was there and she was just minding her own business, as I was, so not much to report there.

author: ashvin nagi

Hi ashvin nagi, we‚Äôre sorry to hear about your experience with our staff. This is not the level of service we strive for, and we sincerely apologize if we‚Äôve fallen short. We appreciate your feedback and will look into this to ensure better service and consistency in our policies.

If you‚Äôre open to sharing more details, we‚Äôd love to understand your concerns better. Please feel free to reach out to us directly‚Äîwe truly value your input and want to improve. 

Thank you for bringing this to our attention.

author: Jayvinn Wong
text:
Came here on a weekend at 9am, and there were only 5 other people here.

Tldr: Great equipment for limited space, but v warm if you come early in the morning (before the aircon kicks in).

+ Limited space but they fit in a great selection of equipment. All the essential machines, cables, 2 full racks with attached platforms, and 3 addition half racks, as well as crossfit equipment like kettlebells.
+ Attached toilet and changing room facilities.
+ Plenty of sanitizing sprays and wipes provided.

- Came here during unstaffed hours, so no comment on service. However, the air conditioning was noticably lacking, with the room being very warm. It became better around 10.30am, so perhaps the air conditioning is on a timer.

author: Chua Weijun
text:
Do do do do do read the term and conditions when signing up with anytime fitness Yishun. I didn‚Äôt really read the term and conditions and took what the salesperson said as granted. As a result I am unable to cancel my membership as promised.

When signing up for the membership I told the person who liaised with me that I am sort of injured, I am worried that by signing up 2 years package I might not be able to sustain throughout the entire duration. I was reassured that I can cancel my membership foc if I have a doc memo.

True indeed I torn my meniscus in the midst of gyming. As such I was force to pause at a rate of close to 40/mth for few months before they finally agree to freeze my membership foc.

Subsequently I unfreeze my membership with the hope that I can return back to gym but my body really can‚Äôt take it. My physio recommended me to stop gyming and start swimming. I tried to ask them if I can cancel my membership with a physio memo and they of course rejected it. They say they can only accept doctor memo be it specialist or GP. Cancel with a fee of 107 sgd. I am actually okay with it cause of sort of give up in anytime fitness salesman and I requested if to head down with a audio recorder to record this and share with my friends. Just to warn them about some sales techniques. This is when they got aggressive. All good though cause I will still write a full blown article about this and share it soon!

Take care when signing up. Think twice!

author: Sihan Goi
text: Came here for a lunchtime workout at around 1230pm and it was quite quiet, with 2 staff at the door. The gym is quite small, though there are 2 levels. The bottom level has 2 squat racks with attached platforms, 2 Eleiko competition PL bars, 3 hybrid bars that spin quite well, 2 sets of colour bumper plates, more rubberized plates, a smith machine, cardio equipment, and cable machines. The platform area is very cramped, and it looks like they barely squeezed everything there, so you people who wish to access the stairs that side will need to step over the platform. Upstairs, there's a studio for stretching, dumbbells up to 50kg and benches, some other machines, and bathrooms. All in all, the equipment and facilities are quite new and clean and the crowd wasn't that much (perhaps because it was raining). Service was also pretty good - I left my water and shaker bottles there after training and was able to WhatsApp them with prompt replies, and was able to pick them up later in the day.

author: Sze Chuan Tan
text:
Decent gym in terms of size and availability of equipment.

Reviews about its run-downness is true, I didn't really mind so long things are working properly. I would have given a 4-star but...

I have to knock away 2 stars because of some safety issues. One very big minus point is the wear and tear that can potentially cause injury to users. For example, I tried using a wrist strap to a cable machine and it came off while I was pulling heavy weight. Then I realised the velcro was so worn out that it couldn't be secured properly.

Another minus point is having the power racks with the pull-up bars just directly below the beams of light. Tried to do pull-ups and a beam hit my head because I didn't expect an obstruction in the way.

text:
Too bad I took a video & not any photos and somehow am unable to load the video up probably because of the size? But anyways I have been to a few Anytime Fitness gyms here albeit not even 1/4 of all they have in SG. But so far this is hands down the best AF gym I have been to here in SG.

They have enough space to make you feel comfortable; they have a huge array of equipment, machines and free weights. They have many different sorts of bars for free weight exercises. They have machines I have never seen in SG throughout my years of being a gym rat.

Staff are helpful and friendly as well which is a huge plus of course. All in all this gym definitely deserves a 5 upon 5 star rating. They have a few machines & cables out of order but I have spoken to the trainers who told me they have already requested for replacements/repairs. That would only increase their already superb gym. In any case the machines they already have which are in order are already more than enough & more than in any other gym I‚Äôve seen here in SG. For the time being this is my favorite AF gym here in SG! Will continue trying new branches out but I feel this would be a tough one to beat!

text:
Cleanliness: 5/5
Everything is clean and very new. What i like is there is always a cleaner helping to clean up the gym every now and then. And i love the lemongrass scent you guys used in the gym. Very refreshing.

Equipment: 4/5
The equipment in my opinion is a little limited due to space but it is generally okay (could be abit of an issue during peak hours). They are very very new by the way.

Shower/Toilet: 4.5/5
Also another thumbs up for the showers - omg i love the shampoo and shower gels you guys supply. They have separate female and male toilets; 2 unisex showers, and a small dressing room with dyson hairdryer! I personally thought there should at least be a common washing basin.

author: Vivian Han
text:
Terrible Service and Poor Communication at Anytime Fitness Jurong East

I had an extremely disappointing experience with Anytime Fitness Jurong East regarding my membership cancellation. About a month ago, their staff informed me that I needed to book a face-to-face appointment to cancel my membership and serve the required 1-month notice period. I followed their instructions, scheduled the appointment, and thought everything was settled.

Fast forward to today‚Äîmy last day of membership‚Äîand I was suddenly informed that they couldn‚Äôt process the cancellation from their end. Instead, I was told at the last minute that I needed to liaise with my home club to finalize the cancellation.

This is completely irresponsible and unprofessional. Why wasn‚Äôt this communicated earlier? Why ask me to come down for an appointment if they couldn‚Äôt handle the process? It‚Äôs a waste of my time and reflects poor management and coordination.

I expected much better service from a gym of this scale. Extremely dissatisfied and would not recommend this branch to anyone looking for reliability and professionalism.

author: Jonathan Williams
text:
I've been a proud member of Anytime Fitness New Tech Park for the past 2 years and I couldn't be happier with my experience. The gym has a fantastic workout atmosphere that really motivates me to push myself during my sessions.

The staff at Anytime Fitness New Tech Park are incredibly friendly and welcoming. They always greet me by name, and happy to have a chat at point of time. The staff's positive attitude is a big part of what makes this gym such a great place to work out.

The gym is equipped with a wide variety of high-quality workout machines and free weights. Whether I'm in the mood for some cardio, strength training, or functional fitness, I'm always able to find the perfect equipment to meet my needs. The equipment is well-maintained and the gym is always clean and organised.

Overall, I highly recommend Anytime Fitness New Tech Park to anyone looking for a fantastic gym experience. The great workout atmosphere, friendly staff, and excellent equipment make this one of the best fitness centers in the area. I look forward to continuing my fitness journey at Anytime Fitness New Tech Park.

author: Julian Ang
text:
Editing my review yet again.

Giving credit where it's due. JJ the sr mgr called me after the latest review i gave below. As well as to follow on my request to cancel my anytime fitness membership. He did an excellent job listening and accepting my perspectives whilst maintaining his professionalism on club management policies. Just for that, I'm bumping this place back to 3 stars. Unfortunately, it's too late for me, and I'm not prepared to reconsider my cancelling my membership.
---
The latest iteration of an operations team has frankly taken anal retentive-ness to a whole new level. Instead of actually calling out behaviour that inconveniences clients' use of facilities they call out behaviour and enforce rules that impinge on the EGOs and ultimately selfish dignity of complaining whiners. Extremely hypocritical and terrible leadership. You choose to assuage the egos of whiners over the actual functionality of a gym. Snail trails, coffee cups in corners, syringes in the stalls are ok but someone rolling out his lats with his shirt off, in a corner of the studio away from the main gym floor, coz the shirt gets rolled up as well, is oh-so-wrong. Please get your priorities straight.

The equipment here is fantastic and the gym space too, but you'd think the place is run by staff who simply don't pay attention.

author: Kay
text:
I am a regular in Clementi Anytime fitness since 2020 till date. Gym is equipped with large variety of exercise machine to target every muscle groups. It also includes 3 squats/bench press racks, a smith machine and a dedicated deadlift platform to cater peak crowd. The gym has 4 washrooms with shower facilities, which is very handy for people who workout in the morning and head to work/school from gym.

The most valuable aspect I had from Clementi AF was Sean Lim‚Äôs absolute professional personal training/coaching. I met Sean in late 2020, after a slip-disc injury. Sean encouraged focusing on overall strength rather than giving up. And we set goal to improve muscle strength and overall aesthetics.

Sean‚Äôs Approach:

1. Form Correction
* Prioritized proper form over quick progression
* Addressed pre-existing bad habits in exercises
* Resolved strength imbalances through altered routines

2. Progress Management
* Set realistic, achievable targets for both body weight/body fat as well as for exercise weight
* Monitored achievements
* Helped break through plateaus
* Built my confidence and self-belief

3. Adaptability
* Modified routines around injuries/sickness, or during busy periods at work
* Provided sports therapy when needed
* Created enjoyable, varied workouts

4. Nutrition Guidance
* Identified and permanently eliminated some unhealthy calorie sources, and replaced some others with cleaner ones
* Introduced concepts of macros, cutting, and bulking and helped me master them
* Guided on meal preparation, even if I have busy schedules with work

Key Achievements
1. Significant strength improvements:
* Barbell bench press: 60kg ‚Üí 85kg (6 reps)
* Barbell squats: 70kg ‚Üí 105kg (5 reps)
* Conventional deadlifts: 80kg ‚Üí 140kg (5 reps)
2. Reached sub-10% body fat

Some gym members who are sick and wish to work out, cough loudly & openly while working out, spreading germs to other gym members who are there to work out. Very "considerate" huh?

The gym coaches are friendly too!

Just remember to bring your access pass for entry. If not, you're not allow to enter & any member open the door for you will liable a $30 fine for them.

If you have a friend who is a gym member here, ask them to bring you here. So that both of you can work out together!

author: HEI HEI
text:
I recently joined Ace the Place Gym and have had a very disappointing experience.

Last week, I was approached by a trainer who was initially very friendly and corrected my posture. He convinced me to sign a trial package that included three sessions. The first session went well, and the trainer asked me to sign up for another 10 sessions, which I did. We sat down and agreed on Monday and Tuesday at 10 AM for the lessons.

However, on Friday night, the trainer called and said I needed to pay extra for software to track my fitness routine, which I declined.

When Monday came, I arrived at the gym at 10 AM, but the trainer was nowhere to be found. After texting and calling, the trainer informed me that he had rescheduled my sessions to Tuesday and Wednesday without notifying me in advance.

Overall, this gym has been more focused on hard selling unnecessary products rather than providing a consistent and professional training experience. I have only attended one session of PT and paid $1000, which they declined to refund me despite the experience I faced. Oh well, I guess lesson learned here. You have been warned!

I hope they improve their customer service and communication.

Update: The assistant manager of Anytime fitness Ace the Place declined my refund request on 3rd July there was no alternate solution to how my remaining sessions can be ultised.

They said I have insufficient proof that I have made an appointment for Monday and Tuesday and the PT trainer said he had booked me for Tuesday and Wednesday but there was no evidence (no text, no email nothing) they just assume and thinks that you are free on that day without even communicating with their customers. Up to date I have attempted and requested to speak with their manager and today is 8 July I have never heard from them to resolve the matter.

Update update:
Up till today (22 July 2024) there is no answer from them. I‚Äôm forced to bring this matter to CASE to resolve it.

The trainer name is VEEN.
The assistant manager is Daniel Raj.

I‚Äôm looking forward to speak to their manager, but up till today it‚Äôs impossible to speak anyone. No calls, No Text, No emails.
source_file: Anytime Fitness ACE The Place CC_reviews.csv

text:
I loved my time here. The staff were friendly and the equipment is great. Try to avoid late evening if you want a quieter time there.

Unfortunately Anytime Fitness partner with Ezypay. A predatory payments company who charge you late payment fees after one failed payment and have been known to continue charging you after cancellation at Anytime. Please be careful when engaging with a contract with Anytime while they continue to work with Ezypay.

UPDATE: I‚Äôve dropped this from 3 to 2 as even though I called the gym to let them know I wanted to cancel in December I have still been charged for January and February. Depending upon the response will depend upon whether I drop this further.

UPDATE 1: Sooooo my contract is up in February‚Ä¶which means I‚Äôm obliged to pay for January and February. Their response was measured and backed by evidence. So mainly just feel embarrassed right now. However due to their response I figured they earned an extra star.

So I was ignored because he knows I'm a member from another branch and chose to treat me as invisible.

What a customer service you have there, Gordon! Well done! Winning competition is nothing when your nose is so high up in the sky.

2ndly, is the former trainer Wilson (if I remember correctly), short and wear specs. 1 of the most arrogant ego trainer I have ever seen, ask him on certain machine yet he direct me to Gordon and some other regulars there while he himself was just pacing up and down for nothing and as Gordon being himself, walks away and act busy. Lol! What worse was Wilson monopolized the equipment when he and his client was using it! And I was to rush my sets just to let him use as he was standing damn near staring!

Not to mention this 2 clowns even tease their own studio classes' instructors and participants. I walked past them once and they were talking loudly with their friend and mentioned about Zumba class is a joke and ineffective and dont understand why people are still attending it, maybe being stupid.

This branch has the worst trainers I have ever encountered. Not going back to this branch anymore and definitely not recommending to any of my friends.

If you are the owner reading this, probably it's time to educate them or rather, for your gym's sake, sack them.

text:
1. The gym is overcrowded with excessive equipment, making it feel cramped and hard to move around.
2. The weighing scale has been broken for years and still hasn‚Äôt been replaced.
3. Staff are almost impossible to reach, making it difficult to get help when needed.
4. Some equipment is frequently out of order, with repairs seemingly always pending.
5. While joining is straightforward, canceling a membership is extremely frustrating. Staff frequently ignore messages, delay responses, and fail to answer calls during office hours, making the process feel intentionally difficult. They often say you need to contact ‚Äúanother department‚Äù for cancellations, but never provide clear contact information, leaving you in the dark about how to end your membership.
6. Each gym is individually owned and managed separately as of what they write on the website, the review above is only for this gym outlet.

If you are looking for a gym with good support, avoid this outlet.

author: Ian Mak
text:
A wonderful and pristine location for getting an awesome training session! This gym is fully equipped with numerous training equipments that tailor to different population demographics, ranging from powerlifters to bodybuilders, to the weekend warriors and casual lifters!

Being one of the larger Anytime Fitness outlets in Singapore, the facility is spacious and inviting, offsetting one of the common complaint many people have with most training facilities. The staff are also very sociable and accomodating, and are always willing to listen to the members' feedback with regards to any matter. Showering and changing facilities are also significantly more spacious than most other outlets, which adds to the overall comfort and feel of the place as well.

All in all, I cannot recommend Anytime Fitness Chai Chee enough. I have zero regrets on changing my home gym to this outlet, and I intend to stay with this outlet for the rest of time spent training.

He had complained to me about how understaffed his branch is and how he is preparing for some competition, to which I said that he would need some help. His answer was "you mean I need mental help?". Only plus side is 24-hour availability of the gym, and somewhat decent equipment. But with the above experience, I'll think of cancelling and getting out of this place as soon as I can.
