author: Hamid
text:
Lack of signage anywhere within the 4 blocks located there, may make it very hard for some to find it.

Location:
AFCC is located in the building next to Decathlon (on its left), where the Harvey Norman outlet is. Enter via the lift lobby, located at the front of the building. Take the lift to the 2nd floor. Upon exiting the lift, turn left and take a left again. Walk straight down, you'll see AFCC on your right.

Parking:
Parking at Viva B.P. is option 1,but cheaper option would be to turn into the HDB carpark further down the road, from the turn to enter Viva business park.

Layout:
spacious. Floor space quiet well utilized with good placement of equipment, machine and racks.

Equipment:
4 squat racks (if I counted correctly), and plenty of space to do compound movements like deadlift, clean and jerks etc.

Amenities:
this is where, to me honestly, they could have done better. A unisex locker room, is fine. But for a unisex toilet and shower area to be incorporated into the locker area, not such a good idea.
Total lack of privacy as the weight lifting area is right in front of the locker area.
Only 1 water cooler for such a massive gym, is quite a surprise for me personally.
Lack of shelf in the shower area is also quite distressing. No shower screen installed, so the shower area cum changing area will be very wet after someone showers.
Plus point is that there are sinks and mirrors along the wall, with hair dryers.

VERDICT:
All in all, a solid gym and kickass equipment with space (rare in SG).

text:
Decent gym, good location however a bit crowded due to relatively small space.

The reason for the one star review however is that I recently renewed my credit card as it is expiring soon. It was my mistake to not inform AF of the new card, and that is my bad.

However while in the middle of the workout I was approached and literally asked to leave because the payment was not charged that month.

I mean, seriously guys? I'm a member for more than two years and you're asking me to leave because the payment is late by two days?

Even after explaining the situation and asked if I can finish the workout first, the brand ambassador asked me to make a payment to the UEN number of the gym I signed up with. At 10pm at night.

Bro idk what you expect me to do sia call up the franchise owner to ask for UEN? At 10pm at night on a public holiday?

I saw that the brand ambassador were literal kids, decided it's not worth trying to talk reason and left.

Terribly disappointing customer service, absolutely no flexibility or thought given to paying member for years. What a blemish on an otherwise good gym.

author: Michele Chang
text:
Anytime Fitness Tampines West CC is a convenient and accessible gym located in Tampines, Singapore. It offers a range of fitness facilities and services, making it a popular choice for individuals looking to stay active and fit.

The gym is well-equipped with a variety of exercise machines and equipment, catering to different workout preferences and fitness levels. Whether you prefer cardio exercises, strength training, or group fitness classes, Anytime Fitness Tampines West CC has something for everyone. The gym is clean and well-maintained, providing a comfortable and safe environment for workouts.

One of the key advantages of Anytime Fitness is its 24/7 access, allowing members to exercise at their convenience. This flexibility is particularly beneficial for individuals with busy schedules or those who prefer to work out during off-peak hours. The gym also offers secure access, ensuring members can work out with peace of mind.

author: Joel Gwey
text:
I have been a member at Anytime Fitness Nex for a while now, and while I appreciate its convenient location, I must say that the overall condition of the gym could use some improvement.

One of the main issues I have noticed is the maintenance of the equipment. Many of the dumbbells and machines show signs of rust, which is not only unsightly but also raises concerns about their durability and safety. Additionally, the deadlift platforms have noticeable dents, which can affect the proper execution of exercises.

Another area that needs attention is the air conditioning system. The gym tends to be excessively humid, making each session more uncomfortable than it should be. I find myself breaking out in sweat excessively, which hampers my workout experience. Adequate air ventilation would greatly alleviate this issue.

Furthermore, the ventilation in the men's restroom leaves much to be desired. There is a persistent unpleasant smell that seems to linger, making it an unpleasant experience for users. Addressing this issue would greatly improve the overall hygiene and comfort of the facilities.

Considering my experiences at other Anytime Fitness locations, I believe Anytime Fitness Nex could benefit from upgrading their equipment to meet the standards found at other branches. Members deserve well-maintained and modern equipment to enhance their workouts.

I hope that management takes these concerns into consideration and makes the necessary improvements to create a more enjoyable environment for all members.

author: Jared ooi
text:
The worst customer service in a gym sector. If Google allow me to give zero ratings, definitely I will give it.

The gym asked a debt collector to chase me for just a 2 months fail payment. THE MAIN CONCERN was AF send me a letter and asked me to settle this payment amount of $1255.48 which is TEN TIMES of the 2 months fail payment which cost only $176.48 within 7 days and I will be incurred any legal action if I fail to do so. I have clarified with the debt collector that AF claim I have no payment since I joined their membership since July 2022, means their system not able to capture my payment all the while.

Then, I called and WhatsApp to AF Buona Vista and even went down to the outlet. The services made me truly disappointed as they never apologise for the system mistake at first and also they direct offered me to cancel my membership the next, but I need to pay for the cancellation fee as my membership tier was under the minimum term. Here can see they never appreciated me as one of the member and don even care to let go the customer as I holding the lowest tier membership.

I have requested to meet the manager and see how to settle this issue, however the manager made me feel like  don‚Äùt have the sincerity as one of the male staff (who communicate with his manager at the same time on the phone) telling that his manager will be working til 6pm the next day but switched immediate to 430pm after I mentioned I will drop by around 530pm. It seems like fooling around us.

Also, this company also trying to take advantage on me as in like if I really no able to provide the proof of my payment transaction, then means I need to pay the amount that you charged on me ?!!

If anyone of you reading this review or you are one of the membership of AF, pls be alert and be reminded and make sure you have your clear payment record!! If not you will be the next victim.

Total lost trust to this fitness centre.

author: Rainer Ong
text:
As a fitness enthusiast eager to maintain a healthy lifestyle, I recently decided to join Anytime Fitness at City Square Mall. Little did I know that this decision would not only positively impact my health but also provide me with exceptional service that exceeded all my expectations.

My journey with Anytime Fitness began with a warm welcome from the staff as soon as I entered the gym. Their friendly demeanor and willingness to assist made me feel right at home. The atmosphere was inviting, with state-of-the-art equipment neatly arranged, creating a motivating environment for a workout.

One aspect that truly stood out to me was the personalized attention I received from the trainers. Unlike other gyms where you are just another number, at Anytime Fitness, the trainers took the time to understand my fitness goals and tailored a workout plan specifically for me. Their expertise and constant encouragement not only pushed me to work harder but also helped me achieve results I had only dreamt of before.

Moreover, the cleanliness and maintenance of the facilities at City Square Mall were impeccable. The gym was spotless, equipment well-maintained, and hygiene standards were top-notch. This attention to detail not only reflected the professionalism of the staff but also ensured a comfortable and safe workout environment for all members.

Apart from the excellent facilities and training programs, another aspect that made my experience at Anytime Fitness unforgettable was the sense of community within the gym. I had the opportunity to participate in group fitness classes where I met like-minded individuals who shared the same passion for fitness. The camaraderie and support from fellow members created a positive and inclusive atmosphere that motivated me to push my limits and strive for my fitness goals.

In addition to the exceptional service and facilities, the convenience of having access to the gym 24/7 was a game-changer for me. Whether it was an early morning workout before work or a late-night session to de-stress, knowing that I could hit the gym anytime suited my busy schedule perfectly.

In conclusion, my experience at Anytime Fitness, City Square Mall, has been nothing short of phenomenal. The dedication of the staff, the high-quality facilities, the personalized training, and the sense of community have all played a significant role in not only transforming my fitness journey but also making it an enjoyable and rewarding experience. Anytime Fitness has truly set a benchmark in providing exemplary service, and I am grateful to be a part of such a remarkable fitness community.

author: Juliana Seng
text:
Goods
- Threadmills are new. As well as the kind reminder sticker to not spray disinfecting liquid on the screen.
- Dumbbells are not rusty.

Bads
- Barbells looks very rusted.
- Plastic leather cover on some equipment looks worn out. Doesnt affect functionality, but can consider replacing.
- Only 2 bench press in front of the dumbbell racks and the minimal space in front of the mirror.
- Only 2 toilet with shower and 1 changing room
- Some fans at the corner are black with dust and in need of a wash.

Unacceptable
- I went at 840am, walked in and my first impression is that outside is way cooler than inside. Unbelievable. I searched for any aircon remote lying around, but alas, there was none.

The aircon looks like it is running, there are helpful paper strips stuck on the aircon to show that wind is indeed blowing out from the unit. The little paper strips just tells me that the aircon has been an ongoing problem.

As I run on the threadmill, some (conspiracy) theories floated in my mind. Maybe the aircon is centralized and the shopping mall has not turned it on yet. Maybe the aircon is on fan mode and not cool mode, and the management want to save aircon money. 9am, 915am, no signs of any centralised aircon switching on. There are more people and it is getting warmer and stuffier and I feel abit light headed. Maybe the oxygen in the room is decreasing too. Cant take it anymore, gonna hop over to another AF outlet.

On my way out, I pop over to the little employee office and asked if the aircon has always been like this. They mentioned they are aware of the issue, it is abit humid and are going to fix it.

Yeah, it is extremely warm, humid, stuffy and fixing it needs to be a top priority. Recommend they get portable aircon. And I am really salty that the employee office, enclosed in its glass walls and separated from the perspiring humans outside, is more cooling. Angry emoji.

I usually workout at AFGB in the early mornings before dawn. I gave 4 stars as AFGB is located inside Kolam Ayer CC, which means that all toilets are locked up until 10am (as written on a sign outside the toilet by the CC).If you need a toilet for nature calls (or a shower after gym to go to work, not sure if there are showers in there)... You're screwed.

I hope AFGB can work something out with the CC, perhaps having a key for the toilets kept inside the gym that members can use for emergency needs.

**EDIT: I went again today and noticed there was indeed a key for the toilets. Changing my 4 star review to a 5 star. Sorry!

author: Su
text: I have been an Anytime Fitness member for so many years. And I have been to so many different clubs in Singapore. Sometimes when I forget to bring the key, I can just give the staff my keyfob number and they will assist to check it in the system and let me go in (for once or twice, of course not all the time) even though I might not be the member of that particular club. This time I told the staff at the North Point club that I forgot the key because I came straight after work and I stay in SengKang which is very far from Yishun for me to go back and grab the key. And this is my first time forgetting the key at that club. But the staff was very rude and he didn‚Äôt assist me at all. The staff just kept repeating that ‚Äúthis is the policy and I can‚Äôt help‚Äù. I can understand that it is the policy. However if that‚Äôs the standard policy, why other staffs/other clubs can close one eye and help out the members who have reasonable explanation just to keep a long term member happy? And it‚Äôs not like I cannot prove/he cannot check that I am the active member. In their system, they can clearly see that I am an active member and why is it so hard to just let me in for one time? Their service in helping a member out is just so bad.

author: Clement Sim
text:
This is one of my favourite branches of Anytime Fitness in Singapore for numerous reasons.

1. The variety of weights and equipment is incredible including three squaring racks, a Smith machine, a whole set of dumbbells and all the machines you can possibly need for a great workout.
2. The staff are extremely friendly and professional! Always pleasant to interact with them.
3. The location is great and easily accessible.
4. All the equipment are well-maintained and safe.
5. The changing rooms are clean with both showers and toilets available.
6. There are sufficient day shelves for you to use.
7. They always play great music (at least for me).

While I need to travel a fair bit to this outlet from home, this has been and always will be my preferred gym if I have the time to spare!

author: Murukesan Arunachalan
text: Your gym is exceptional. The state-of-the-art equipment and well-maintained facilities provide a comfortable environment for all levels of fitness. The staff are knowledgeable, friendly, and invested in helping clients reach their goals. Personal trainers are attentive and create custom workout plans. The community is inclusive and diverse, with a supportive atmosphere that motivates individuals to achieve their fitness goals. I highly recommend your gym for anyone seeking a top-notch fitness facility with a welcoming environment.

One of the highlights of this gym is its 24/7 access, allowing members to work out at any time that suits their schedule. The membership fees are affordable, making it a great option for those on a budget. Overall, Anytime Fitness Tampines West Community Club is a great choice for those looking for a convenient and affordable gym in the Tampines area

author: Fahd Siddiqui
text:
I have been visiting quite a few different AF outlets since my home gym is under renovation and I personally believe AF TP is the best in Singapore when all things are considered.
- Firstly toilets,shower and changing rooms are well integrated into the gym and have decent amount of space.
- Although it's in the heart of Singapore they don't comprise on space or equipment so it doesn't feel like your constantly squeezing around the gym.
- Plenty of benches and dumbbells which are usually the most used equipment so it's unlikely you will have to wait to use them.
- Extremely friendly staff
- Clean gym and availability of wipes to clean ur equipment
- Extra accessories in the gym available like many different cable accessories, weight belt and foam rollers( Only missing the double rope which city hall has)
If your in need of a gym in the city or near work this is the best option also conveniently located above Tanjong pagar MRT.

author: Jayvinn Wong
text:
Tldr: The best AF gym in CCK, with lots of well maintained equipment, spacious layout, and clean environment.

My favourite gym in CCK, which is very well taken care of by management and members. The premises are well ventilated and pleasant smelling, without any dust lying around. When I came down in the morning, I saw a cleaner lady meticulously wiping and dusting, kudos to her! Gym members also have the habit of wiping down equipment after use. The aircon was spoilt a few months ago, but it's back now!

The equipment available is quite standard, with 2 full racks, 1 deadlift platform, 1 smith machine, and 1 hack squat machine. They also have the plate loaded low row and incline press machines, which are more unique.

One thing to note is that the toilet facilities and water cooler are outside the gym. This gym also does not have a plate loaded leg press :(

But overall, a superb gym!

I‚Äôve been training with Zac at Anytime Fitness for a year, and I can't recommend him highly enough. His consistency and knowledge have made a significant impact on my fitness journey. Zac takes the time to understand each individual‚Äôs goals and tailors workouts accordingly, ensuring I stay motivated and challenged. His guidance on form and technique has not only helped me avoid injuries but also allowed me to see real progress‚ÄîI've gained strength and improved my overall fitness.

However, I do have some feedback regarding the gym‚Äôs equipment. The hand swings equipment is quite old, and there‚Äôs only one in the entire gym. It often feels out of place, especially given the quality of Zac's instruction. An upgrade or additional options for this equipment would enhance the overall experience.

In summary, while Zac is an exceptional instructor who delivers results, an investment in better equipment would elevate the gym experience even further.

author: Steve Demers
text:
Let me tell you a story of why you shouldn't use this location at HV2 and I never will again - I'll be telling everyone I know who lives around here too.

I travel a lot and make use of many different gyms abroad .

I've had an Anytime Fitness membership so that I can use their facilities when they are available abroad.  Often there's one nearby, I've never had a bad experience - until this one.

This location is actually near to my home but have never bothered to use it because our condo gym is decent and convenient to use by just walking downstairs.

Recently I decided to check out it though, maybe there's a couple of exercises that can add to my routines that would be beneficial.

After a very short time there I began to see the degradation of this facility.
Machines that seem to be perpetually broken, water fountain that is out of service, washrooms with equipment that just had a sign on them indicating they'll never be repaired, replaced or removed.

It's a bit of a dirty gym too.
There's layers of dirt in the corners from nobody cleaning for long periods.
There's spray bottles on the equipment with little rags to wipe with - but after a few days of seeing the exact same rags not being replaced or cleaned - I could tell that they seldom get changed out.  Several of them are brown from mildew and dirt...gross.

Pretty much every piece of padded equipment is fraying at the stitch seams.

This place may have been in good shape when HV2 opened but it's been maintained poorly.

Notwithstanding all of that I went for a few days because my membership is set to expire at the end of the month and I wanted to decide whether or not to renew again.  If I did then I'd start using this location.

Well...my last visit assisted in making that decision for me!

When attempting to use the cable rack I noticed a badly failed carabiner.  I'm sure you're familiar with them and what they do - also what a failed unit looks like.
This one wasn't returning to the lock position on its own after changing out grips.
This is a horrible accident waiting to happen, if someone uses it and it snaps (which they certainly do) it'll injure that poor soul very badly.

Having seen this before my 30 years of gym training I took off and went to see about getting a new one from the staff - whom the door says are available from 10 am.

I've asked for these to be replaced before at other gyms and they always have them available just in case - they're cheap equipment that is important.  It's good to have spares right?

It was 11 am - there was nobody to be seen.  So I placed the carabiner on the staff door handle.

At 11:18 I noticed a staff member came in.  While he was getting his keys out to unlock the staff office he saw the carabiner and picked it up to look at it.

I went over to explain where it came from and to ask for another one - I'd be happy to place it.

He hands it back to me saying that it's fine to use and that all I have to do is move the lock mechanism over by hand every time.

This was a bit shocking.  He was telling me to just keep using the dangerous failed carabiner!
I insisted that it should not be used and told him that someone could get hurt.  Still he told me it's fine.

I argued that a gym shouldn't have this sort of injury liability in their facility and he finally took it from my hand with a very grumpy look and mumbled something about getting one online.

Asking him how long it will take to be replaced he said with a very annoyed look that he had no idea and that he'll have to find somewhere to "source" one.

This was surprising!  Not only did this gym not have one but seemed reluctant to even place it on a priority so that members can continue use the facility fully.

As a joke and a test to see how far this will go I told the now angry looking fellow that "How about I just buy one with my own money and bring it in then?"

He was quite agreeable to this with a "okay that sounds good"

I'm not doing that!
Thank you Marcus for helping me decide to not renew my membership.

author: Lionel Lee
text:
One of the best Anytime Fitness gyms in Singapore: location is central (within the CBD area), premise is spacious and clean, well-lit and features seating area, showers, and locker facilities. Equipment-wise, everything is well-maintained and boasts a wide range of machines and racks that provide options for casual gym goers to bodybuilders and everyone else in between.

The trainers there are mostly experienced and warm: many of them are happy to give you a hand with the equipment adjustments or even workout tips. My personal recommendation is Amirr - he's not only a fitness and nutrition maven, but also provides services in muscle release massage and injury recovery too.

author: Thomas Ting
text:
Arguably the best AF in Singapore.

For starters, this AF is massive, and that means plenty of weights, machines, cardio and workout areas. This means that you no longer have to keep hovering around power racks waiting for the next guy to finish his sets.

General upkeep of the place is good, with minor wear as expected of any commercial gym. Locker and restroom facilities are basic but good (can't expect Pure Fitness facilities, and that's not what most gym goers are looking for).

Accessibility is excellent, about a 5 minute walk from Pasir Panjang MRT.

All in all, I'm impressed enough with this gym that I'm seriously considering making this my regular gym even though it is slightly out of the way for me.

author: Shihao Foo
text:
My favourite gym for a late night chill workout. The gym is relatively new and so the equipment and facilities are clean and fresh. The lighting isn‚Äôt too bright either. Overall the decor has the relaxing vibes of a bar.

+ve: training wise, it also has some less common machines that other AFs don‚Äôt have. For example, its assisted pullup machine is of the standing type (unlike the more common kneeling type). They also provide a helpful chart of their crowd levels at different times of the day (busiest between 7-9+pm on weekdays).

-ve: the biggest downside for me is that the gym has a no chalk policy, hence i only come for less intense workouts where i will not need chalk. Another point is that although the gym is well equipped, somehow I was not able to find a single abs crunch machine.

Finally as a more neutral point, for folks looking to train their glutes, i initially couldn‚Äôt find a booty builder machine here, but then I realised they have an equivalent called ‚Äúglute drive‚Äù. To me, the booty builder looks more aesthetic, but this equivalent looks functionally similar. Have not tried it though.

author: Jeremy Chan
text:
Went to this gym for the 1st time today because I had events in that area earlier. I went during the peak hour though, around 6pm & was there till about 9pm.

Did not take any pictures as I believe there are sufficient pictures of this gym now. The only thing that made me feel a little meh was how packed the gym was. But notwithstanding, it‚Äôs understandable since it was during peak hours. My favorite Anytine Fitness gym is the one at City Hall but even for that gym I never go during peak hours because the crowd gets super crazy, even worse than this gym during peak hour even though the City Hall gym is bigger.

Nevertheless, I still enjoyed my session at the gym today and I got to do everything I needed to do without waiting much. They have some pretty obscure equipment which is a thumbs up for sure. Hack squat machines they do have at other AF gyms albeit not many, but it was the 1st time I saw a belted squat machine at any AF gyms.

In summary, this was definitely a nice gym and even though I said the peak hour dampened my mood a little, I‚Äôm still giving it 5 stars as it deserves the rating I feel. On a side note, many many MANY years ago I was a member of Fitness First for many years and used to move around to the different FF gyms and the Metropolis FF gym was 1 of the gyms I frequented quite often. Passing it today though it looks sad & desolate. Hahahaha! I guess AF took a number of their customers away. Lol. Nice gym to go to if you‚Äôre in that area! I stay central/east so this isn‚Äôt exactly close to me, the City Hall AF is super close hence it being my favourite. But if I‚Äôm ever in the area I wouldn‚Äôt hesitate to go to this AF!

If you‚Äôre considering joining, be aware of how poorly they handle cancellations and communication. I‚Äôm now forced to demand a refund for the October fee and am considering legal action if this isn‚Äôt resolved. Absolutely disappointed with the way this was handled. Stay away from this gym if you value transparency and good customer service!

author: Hung Hao
text:
Mixed feelings- this is an awesome place for those hustling for a narly leg pump. With a myriad of leg day machines, even the famed Hack Squat, I would love to come here for a leg day workout!

There is certainly more than enough machines here to tickle any fancy. I think that it is rather spacious, and also I went at the peak and did not find it crowded.

Another plus point would be the two vending machines, one with purely drinks, and another one with more protein based beverages.

However, there are certain things that I found lacking.

Firstly, free weight dumbbells only go up to the maximum weight of 40kg, and surprisingly, the pair of 37.5kgs were missing.  Colour me confused, as I expected dumbbells to usually hit about 50kg in max weight. Not that I use those, but still, probably important for the big guy right?

Secondly, the toilet seemed rather dirty when I used it. Again, not the end of the world and certainly not a reflection of the outlet. But it would be nice to figure that out.

author: Timothy Studlo
text: I have been a patron of the brand Anytime Fitness for seven years and visited many outlets throughout the world. Anytime Fitness Tanjong Pagar outlet is one the best I have ever visited worldwide. In the past three months this outlet has had a complete overhaul of the entire gym  with new facilities, all brand new equipment, and new staff. The atmosphere is friendly, clean, engaging, and conducive for a top quality workout. The staff is super helpful providing you assistance at the drop of a hat. If you're looking for a trainer look no further. Anytime Fitness has some of the most knowledgeable and caring trainers you can find (I recommend Mansor). They're focused on you the entire time you train helping you to achieve your goal. They also use data driven metrics (body composition analyser machine) to analyse your progress and differentiate your workout to your individual needs. The gym offers plenty of space so it never feels crowded and it runs 24/7 so you can find a time that works for you. Finally, this is a gym that welcomes all types of people form beginners to experienced gym rats, from young to old, guys and girls. It's really place were you don't feel intimated and you can do your work! Thanks Any Time TP you guys rock!

text:
I‚Äôve been using this gym for almost two years, and it has been a fantastic experience. The gym is well-maintained, spacious, and equipped with high-quality machines and free weights, making it a great place for both beginners and experienced lifters.

Colon and Ryan are incredibly friendly, knowledgeable, and approachable. The gym has an energizing atmosphere, with great music and a supportive community that fosters a positive vibe.

The class offerings are impressive as well, with a variety of options ranging from strength training to yoga, zumba and many more. Personal training services are also available for those looking for extra guidance.

Overall, I‚Äôd say d‚ÄôArena AF is a top-notch fitness center that offers everything needed for a great workout experience. Highly recommend it to anyone looking for a gym that is well-equipped, clean, and welcoming. üëçüèªüëçüèª

author: Su Hui
text:
My initial experience was great. I‚Äôve heard horror stories of members who had issues cancelling their membership with other AF branches and was assured it wouldn‚Äôt happen here. I signed up for 18 months and was relatively happy throughout, the people are nice. However, when it came time to cancel my membership, they kept delaying their response and didn‚Äôt want to furnish me with the form to confirm the cancellation. I was constantly asked to go down to their gym and asked why I wanted to cancel (when I had already given my reasoning a few times both on text and in person). After much chasing I finally got the cancellation form and was assured that January will be my final billing month.

Today (1st February) my credit card was charged and I am appalled at the service of this gym. I‚Äôve reached out to their team and hope their service recovery will redeem them.

Just to be clear, AF is great if you have no intentions to leave. It‚Äôs only problematic when you try to cancel your membership. I have been highly dissatisfied with the cancellation process and communication hence the low rating.

author: ÈªÑÊñáÂø†
text:
Worst gym experience ever. I went to check out the place before signing up, and the staff barely paid attention to me. They seemed uninterested and acted like they were doing me a favour by answering my questions. That should have been my first red flag.

I still decided to join, thinking maybe the facilities would make up for it. Big mistake. The equipment is always occupied, and some machines are either broken or not well-maintained. The worst part? The cancellation process. It‚Äôs not straightforward at all. You have to email them after your contract ends, and if anything goes wrong, you‚Äôre charged again. Plus, they require one month‚Äôs notice. It just feels like they‚Äôre making it as difficult as possible to leave.

At almost $100 per month, I expected way better. The staff are unprofessional, the gym is overcrowded, and the whole experience is just frustrating. Definitely not worth it.

author: Boom Boom
text:
I wouldn‚Äôt recommend Anytime Fitness to anyone. Joining is effortless, but leaving? That‚Äôs a whole different story. They don‚Äôt let you cancel easily‚Äîyou have to email them after your contract ends, and if anything goes wrong with that email, you‚Äôre forced to keep paying. On top of that, they require a 30-day notice, which is just ridiculous. Why make it so difficult for people to leave?

The gym itself isn‚Äôt worth the stress. It‚Äôs a lot of money per month, yet the service is disappointing. The staff aren‚Äôt helpful, and I‚Äôve seen complaints about rude behaviour. A gym should be welcoming, not frustrating.

If you‚Äôre considering joining, think twice. Getting in is easy, but getting out feels like a trap.

text:
I've been training at Anytime Fitness West Coast for over two months now, and I just want to give a big shoutout to my personal trainer, David. I have a torn meniscus and my knee tends to get inflamed very easily, so I was initially quite hesitant about strength training. But David has been incredibly attentive and knowledgeable‚Äîalways adjusting the workouts to suit my condition while still helping me make real progress.

Over the past couple of months, I‚Äôve noticed a big improvement‚Äîmy knee gets less inflamed, and my leg feels noticeably stronger. I‚Äôm really happy with the results so far and grateful for the care and guidance I‚Äôve received.

Also, I really like this outlet‚Äîit‚Äôs spacious, clean and well-equipped, which makes the training experience even more comfortable and enjoyable. Highly recommend David and this location if you‚Äôre looking for a supportive and effective training environment, especially if you‚Äôre working with an injury or need a more tailored approach.

author: Ho Hweeying
text:
I will not be giving even a star! This is the worst service I have ever received. I was charged a failed payment fee of $15.26 due to an issue with auto-debit. This occurred because I had to cancel my card immediately after it was compromised, and the cancellation coincidentally fell close to the auto-billing date, resulting in the failed payment fee. I contacted AF via text and email to request a waiver of the fee, but I was told it could not be waived as the fee was generated by EZYPAY (the system AF uses for billing). This is ridiculous!

Despite this, I made my payment through PayNow, as I have not yet received my new card. I sent them proof of the payment via WhatsApp, and they replied, 'Your membership still has an outstanding balance for this month.'

Correct me if I'm wrong, but can I interpret this to mean that since the payment was made via PayNow or any other method besides auto-debit, AF will have to manual update the system. Does this also mean they can waive the failed payment fee if they are willing to.

I would say AF is taking granted of our membership. They are not even appreciate their members. We are paying our membership fee every single month, without us signing up as member, AF is nothing!

TLDR: AF is a money-sucking gym with ZERO empathy

author: Jairaj Jeyabal
text:
Visited this gym for the first time yesterday and I was highly impressed right from the moment I entered.

Very friendly and helpful staff who greet you at the door as you enter. Good organisation of equipment, really spacious layout as well. This gym is catered towards powerlifters and strength athletes. They have a unique collection of plate-loaded machines which are hard to come by anywhere else. If you love to lift heavy, this is certainly the spot for you.

There is a custodian/cleaner who maintains the place well. He's always wiping down the equipment. No issues with other users, positive vibes all around.

If you are in the area, you have to check out this gym. Easily accessible from Jurong East MRT, it's a 5 minute walk (sheltered too) from there.

author: Nina Natasha Hamidi
text:
The staff is friendly and helpful, especially during staffed hours, and the gym has a welcoming, non-intimidating atmosphere. It's not overcrowded, which means I rarely have to wait to use equipment. I also appreciate the global access to other Anytime Fitness locations, which is great for travel.

If there‚Äôs one downside, it‚Äôs that the size of the gym and the range of amenities can vary greatly depending on the location. Some locations are more spacious and better equipped than others, so it's worth checking out your local branch before signing up.
Overall, I'd recommend Anytime Fitness to anyone looking for a convenient, no-frills gym with flexible hours and a supportive community vibe.

text:
The gym is decent and in a good spot, but it‚Äôs often crowded and the music is way too loud.

The real issue? I forgot to update my card details after getting a new one ‚Äî my bad. But two days after the failed payment, I got pulled aside mid-workout, told to leave, and fined. I‚Äôve been a member for several years, and they couldn‚Äôt even let me finish my session?

Even after explaining, the staff insisted I pay immediately via UEN ‚Äî at 10pm on a public holiday. How was I supposed to get that info then? The staff were clearly just kids so I decided to just walked out.

Really disappointing service with no flexibility at all. A shame, because the gym itself is fine. But I wouldn‚Äôt recommend it.

author: anas syakir
text:
If you‚Äôre looking for a gym that feels like family, look no further and that‚Äôs largely thanks to Leonard. From the moment you walk in, Leonard doesn‚Äôt just greet you he welcomes you like a brother coming home. His warmth, genuine care, and unshakeable positivity transform what could be just another workout space into a true second home.

Leonard treats everyone equally whether you‚Äôre a new member or a regular with respect, kindness, and infectious enthusiasm. He remembers your name, asks about your day, and celebrates your progress like it‚Äôs his own victory. There‚Äôs no ego here, just pure support. He doesn‚Äôt see members as clients he sees them as a friend.

What sets Leonard apart isn‚Äôt just his professionalism, which is top-tier but his ability to make every interaction meaningful. He‚Äôll encourage you when you‚Äôre struggling, share a laugh when you need it, and always make time to listen. You never feel like just another face in the crowd you feel seen, valued, and truly cared for.

The gym can be an intimidating place for many, but Leonard dissolves that fear instantly. He radiates a vibe of acceptance and camaraderie that makes you want to show up. It‚Äôs rare to find someone who embodies the spirit of community like he does. He doesn‚Äôt just work here he builds a home here, one smile, one conversation, one act of kindness at a time.

Leonard, you‚Äôre not just staff you‚Äôre the soul of this gym. Thank you for making every workout feel like a reunion with family. This place wouldn‚Äôt be the same without you.

They got the standing tables blocking up space across the whole gym from when the place used to be a bowling lounge or something so they work around the structures from prior leases for an even worse placement of gym equipment.

author: Bryan Bernadind
text:
Beware, This gym appears to be shutting down!

They‚Äôve done away with the purple wet wipe stands, which is a serious hygiene concern‚Äîespecially with Covid and flu making the rounds again. The tap at the basin has been leaking for ages, and no one seems remotely interested in fixing it. Word has it the cloths used on the machines are washed perhaps once a week, if it is even washed at all?!

Oh, and remember the complimentary fruits on Fridays between 11am and 8pm for Members‚Äô Day? That‚Äôs quietly faded that out too. It now randomly appears like a mythical creature.

Staff behaviour leaves much to be desired‚Äînot helping to organize the gym for members, asking and pressuring members to make fake review in exchange for old freebies, lengthy smoke and lunch breaks, vaping just outside the entrance (which, let‚Äôs not forget, is against the law in Singapore). New hires like Carmen and Bernice seem blissfully unaware of even the most basic standards of customer service. The overall attitude? Utterly lacking in professionalism. The staff often laugh and talk loudly and blast the music. This is very distasteful.

Don‚Äôt bother referring a friend‚Äîthey‚Äôre unlikely to honour the free month, regardless of what‚Äôs promised.

But then again, it‚Äôs hardly a surprise. As one reviewer aptly put it, this is easily one of the worst Anytime Fitness outlets in Singapore. And those glowing reviews? Likely penned by the staff themselves.

Beware everyone and run!

text:
AF New Queensway is honestly such a great gym. The first thing I noticed when I joined was how clean everything is. The floors, the machines, even the bathrooms are always spotless. It just makes the whole experience so much nicer when you‚Äôre working out in a space that‚Äôs clearly well taken care of.

The staff here are also amazing. They always say hi when you walk in, and they‚Äôre super friendly and approachable. I‚Äôve asked a few questions about the equipment and my membership, and they‚Äôve always been happy to help without making you feel like you‚Äôre bothering them. It gives the gym a really welcoming vibe.

There‚Äôs also a really solid range of equipment, whether you're lifting, doing cardio, or just stretching out, there‚Äôs more than enough to go around. I‚Äôve rarely had to wait for anything, even during busy times, which is a big plus.

All in all, it‚Äôs just a really good place to train. It‚Äôs clean, the team is great, and it has everything you need. I‚Äôm really happy I joined!

author: Ninja master1140
text:
Came to the gym today , the experience was sub par to a gym standard. The gym was humid and hot , air con was not strong enough. Was already sweating even with the fan blasting at full speed ; training just like old school where air con was non existent.

The gym layout was spacious , functional area was big too but did not have the resistance bands for warm ups or foam rollers to cool down.

Equipment wise - Majority of the cables , weights and kettlebells was SUPER Rusty which might be uncomfortable to work out with due to the amount of metallic rust. Seems the weights and cables was not been properly oiled and cleaned hence a lot of the machines was madly rusted.

Weights - Other then the colour bumpers plates which was ok , the other weighted plates was tearing off and the plates is worn and tear so might need to upgrade.

Water Dispenser - There was a water disruption so need to provide water bottles for members.

Toilets and Showers was cordoned off due to some renovation works so need to use the malls toilets.

Vending Machine - Cans will pop out if drop from heights , therefore will cause the drink to spill out. Not sure how to cushion the drink when it drops after purchasing.

Treadmills - Ok ok

Changing Rooms - Ok Ok

Overall The gym really needs an immediate renovation to upgrade the machines and weights. Too rusty and the carpentry looks updated as compared to other AF Outlets.

Overall Gym - 3/ 10
Machines -  5/10
Humidity - 1/10

Worst AF in the north especially in Yishun.

text:
I have been visiting this gym on weekends over the past 2 years. Although I do not write reviews often, thought of sharing an overall view based on my experience.

Location: extremely good - whether you are using public transportation or driving. I will surely get parking even during the peak hours. Very good foot traffic.

Space: quite a large space and not crowded even during peak times.

Equipment: hardly maintained. There are 3-4  treadmills (out of 8) not working for over 6 months. No efforts made to maintain other equipment too. Old dumbells and machines.

Comfort: recently it seems that there are a big issue with the cooling system. The gym is extremely hot and suffocating. I can see some members fanning themselves or moving close to ceiling fans to cool themselves.

Bathrooms: honestly disgusting to see that the cleaning lady often splashes buckets of water on the floor. Other than that, its ok.

Staff: hardly see any staff in the gym. Whoever is there, remains in the office space. Not proactive or seeking any improvement as I see.

Conclusion: fantastic location but Management must change and a face-lift is urgently required

author: T J
text:
An Outrageous Cash Grab

The new management's actions are more than a "joke"‚Äîthey're a downright insult. They've shamelessly introduced a predatory policy, charging a $10 fee just to issue a receipt, a basic document that should be provided free of charge. This is a transparent attempt to wring every last cent out of their members, especially those who, like you, have been loyal for years.

After spending at least 2-3K with the club over the last 2 years, you were are with a wall of silence. You were forced to chase them relentlessly‚Äîthrough unanswered calls, ignored emails, and unmonitored WhatsApp chats‚Äîjust to get a simple reply. And when they finally deigned to respond, they had the audacity to demand a fee for a service that costs them virtually nothing.

The justification for this extortion is as laughable as it is enraging. They claim that since they're not GST-registered, they aren't required to issue a receipt‚Äîas if a bank statement is a suitable substitute for a multi-thousand-dollar transaction. They're deliberately creating a bureaucratic nightmare, hiding behind flimsy excuses like "a lot of administration work," when they've already confirmed they have all the transaction details on hand.

This is a new low. They know that many of their members need these receipts for corporate benefits, and they're exploiting that necessity for their own gain. This isn't just about a measly $10; it's about a complete disregard for their members and a cynical ploy to profit off of their own inefficiency. It leaves a bitter taste in your mouth to see a company stoop to such a vile level.

author: K T (Kelly)
text:
"Needs Urgent Improvement! Zero Safety, Organization, and Cleanliness"

I've visited three Anytime Fitness locations in Singapore, and this one is the worst.
This is based on about three months of visiting 2-3 times per week. I will be switching to another location from now on.

The biggest issue is that the owner and staff show no signs of wanting to improve.
If you look at the Google Maps reviews, you'll see that most recent low-rated reviews have no reply from the owner. And when there is a reply, it's just a generic "Thank you for your feedback" message. From a user's point of view, nothing is actually improving.

As a result, polite and respectful members are leaving, and only those who need guidance and education remain. That's the real problem.

1. Organization & Cleanliness
Plates are left scattered everywhere after use, and even machine parts are lying around.
Safety bars from benches are not put back, and 20kg barbells lying on the floor seems to be the normal situation here.
The cloths for wiping down machines are always wet and feel unhygienic. I have never seen anyone use them after finishing a machine.
The floor mats near the lat pulldown area are peeling and uneven, which is dangerous. It you cannot fix it right away, at least put up a warning sign.

2. User Manners
Groups of people talking loudly are common (about once every two visits). Their voices are so loud they go through my noise-canceling headphones, which is very distracting.
Also, people do not clean or put equipment back after use. Benches and plates are left out, so the free-weight area often does not have what you need. This means I have to walk between different bench areas to collect plates, which is a waste of time and unsafe.
A bench area with zero 20kg plates? That should never happen.

3. Staff
Staff do greet you, but they do not do enough to keep the gym tidy. Many just sit and scroll on their phones instead of taking action.
They should focus on keeping the gym clean and teaching members basic manners. A few staff pick up abandoned barbells, but most ignore safety and hygiene problems.
Honestly, the owner needs to start with proper staff training.

Bottom line: If you want to train seriously, I do NOT recommend this gym. Go to another Anytime Fitness, even if it's farther away.

author: Sihan Goi
text: Came here over lunchtime from 12 to 2pm on a Wednesday and it was not too crowded. This is a very powerlifting centric gym. There are only power bars - a range of Eleiko, Rogue and HS Power bars. The Rogue are in lbs. There are no hybrid bars nor weightlifting bars, but at least all the bars spin. I lifted with the Rogues - the centre knurlings are brutal. Equipment wise, there are 6 half racks and 2 full racks, 3 platforms, and at least 1 bar per rack/platform. Ziva bumpers (only 10kg, 20kg and a couple 5kg). There are also some old metal PL plates in the office. Loads of plate loaded and cable machines, cardio equipment, a large warmup area. Generally it's huge and open with no narrow corridors or areas, a good layout for a gym. Access is either via lift lobby to the right of Harvey Norman (when you're looking at it), or you can take the stairs/escalators from Harvey Norman to level 2 and exit to go to the gym. There is a shared unisex bathroom with a few female only stalls, sinks and Dyson hair dryers, but there are no toilets in the gym (there are public toilets outside the gym). Quite a nice gym that's well stocked in terms of equipment, but would've liked some WL/hybrid bars at least.

author: Ryan Wong
text:
There are many good gyms across Singapore, but to find a great gym is always a bonus. Anytime Fitness Tanjong Pagar (located within International Plaza) is an example of a great gym: the spacing between equipment is good, the equipment are all generally well-maintained, the staff and fellow gym goers are polite to each other, and I think manager Azri with his team of Personal Trainers do a good job in creating a positive and inclusive environment where members and first timers feel comfortable and safe training at their own pace.

I personally train with Muhammad and he does a phenomenal job of not just training you physically, but he also takes the time and effort to check on your personal wellbeing as well, such as how your food intake is going, and how your stress levels are. There are many good Personal Trainers out there, but a great one like Muhammad is always hard to find.

5 stars for Anytime Fitness Tanjong Pagar, and definitely 5 stars for PT Muhammad!

author: Darren Tan Wei Jie
text:
Nestled in the bustling heart of one of Singapore‚Äôs most established residential districts, Anytime Fitness Bukit Timah Central offers a reliable, accessible, and community-focused gym experience. As part of the globally recognized Anytime Fitness franchise, this outlet upholds the brand‚Äôs commitment to 24/7 access, cleanliness, and member-centric service‚Äîall within a compact yet efficient workout environment.

One of the biggest draws of this location is its convenience. Situated just minutes from the Downtown Line and easily reachable by bus or car, it caters well to nearby residents, working professionals, and students from nearby institutions. The round-the-clock access is especially valuable in Bukit Timah, where busy schedules and long days make flexible workout timing a must.

Despite its relatively modest size compared to flagship gyms, the space is well-designed and makes smart use of layout. You‚Äôll find clearly defined zones for cardio, strength training, and free weights. The gym is equipped with high-quality Life Fitness and Hammer Strength machines, including treadmills, ellipticals, rowing machines, and resistance equipment. Free weights, barbells, and benches are available and kept in good condition.

What sets this gym apart is its tight-knit community vibe. Regulars often praise the welcoming atmosphere, where members greet each other and the staff know people by name. The trainers are approachable and helpful, offering guidance when needed and available for personal training sessions tailored to individual goals.

Group classes and fitness challenges are also part of the experience, helping to create motivation and engagement. These vary seasonally and may include HIIT circuits, functional training, or community runs. The Anytime Fitness app further supports members with virtual workouts and progress tracking‚Äîuseful for those who prefer hybrid training approaches.

Cleanliness and maintenance are well managed. Equipment is sanitized regularly, and cleaning supplies are readily available for member use. The bathrooms and shower facilities are simple but well-kept, ensuring a comfortable experience even during busy hours.

In summary, Anytime Fitness Bukit Timah Central is a well-rounded gym that excels in convenience, community, and consistency. While it may not be the largest fitness facility in the city, it offers everything you need for effective daily training in a welcoming and no-pressure environment. Whether you're just starting your fitness journey or looking for a convenient place to stay in shape, this outlet is a solid choice in the Bukit Timah area.

He answered all my questions clearly, explained the membership options in detail, and made the sign-up feel smooth and stress-free. It‚Äôs always a good feeling walking into a place where the staff are welcoming and genuinely care about helping you out. Big thanks to him‚Äîyou made my start at Anytime Fitness a great one!

author: Ayden Haikel
text:
I‚Äôd like to take a moment to sincerely appreciate one of the standout staff members at Anytime Fitness New Queensway, Ayden. From day one, he‚Äôs made the gym feel like more than just a place to work out, it‚Äôs become a space that feels warm, welcoming, and motivating, all thanks to his energy and effort.

Every time I walk through those doors, without fail, Ayden greets me with a big smile and a friendly ‚ÄúHow‚Äôs it going?‚Äù Even on the days when I‚Äôm dragging my feet in, somehow his energy gives me that boost I need. He doesn‚Äôt just stop at a hello either. He checks in regularly to make sure I‚Äôm enjoying my workouts, the environment, and even the music playing in the background, which somehow is always on point. I swear he‚Äôs got a playlist for every mood.

One thing that always makes me laugh is his classic gym dad joke: ‚ÄúWhy don‚Äôt skeletons ever go to the gym? Because they don‚Äôt have the guts!‚Äù It‚Äôs always delivered with the most serious face, which somehow makes it even funnier.

It‚Äôs the small gestures the check-ins, the consistent positivity, the genuine effort to connect with members that really set Ayden apart. He goes above and beyond to ensure everyone feels comfortable and cared for in the gym, whether you‚Äôre a regular or someone just starting out.

Ayden, thank you for making New Queensway not just a gym, but a community. Keep being awesome!

I‚Äôm so glad I joined Anytime Fitness, especially because of my coach, Coach Wan. They are incredibly knowledgeable, patient, and motivating. From day one, they took the time to understand my goals and created a program that‚Äôs both challenging and realistic.

Training with Coach Wan has not only improved my fitness but also boosted my confidence. I‚Äôm stronger, healthier, and more disciplined ‚Äî all thanks to their guidance and support.

author: Timon Tai
text:
I've been training with Kirtan for over two years now, and I can honestly say he‚Äôs one of the best personal trainers out there. What sets him apart is his deep, holistic understanding of body mechanics. Unlike the typical brute-force, muscle-building approach you get with many trainers, Kirtan focuses on integrating movement, balance, and mobility in a way that makes your body feel stronger and better after every session.

No two workouts are ever the same ‚Äî I haven‚Äôt repeated a single set in all this time. Every lesson is thoughtfully planned, challenging, and fun. And if you ever feel like mixing it up, he also incorporates boxing, which adds another layer of excitement and intensity.

I‚Äôve seen real results, but more importantly, I feel better in my body ‚Äî more aware, more agile, and more resilient. Highly recommend Kirtan to anyone looking for training that‚Äôs intelligent, engaging, and truly transformative.

author: Ally Ong
text:
I‚Äôve been visiting this gym for a while now, and it‚Äôs easily become my happy place. The staff are warm and welcoming, the space is spotless, and the layout is well organized, weights are always perfectly reracked like some behind-the-scenes magic is happening. The equipment is well-maintained it‚Äôs spoiled me for other gyms.

Being right in the heart of the CBD, it does get busy during peak hours - think ‚Äúafter-work drinks‚Äù level of packed. If that‚Äôs not your scene, just tweak your workout time and you‚Äôll have a much smoother experience. The gym is in an older building, which makes its location perfect but also means a little consideration goes a long way: don‚Äôt slam the weights (nobody needs a surprise earthquake drill), and be ready to share machines when it‚Äôs busy.

I train with Mansor, and honestly, it‚Äôs one of the best decisions I‚Äôve ever made. He really knows his stuff and has a sharp eye for safety. Mansor has this rare mix of pushing you to your limits while keeping you grounded, so you‚Äôre not just building a Greek god physique, but also the mental toughness to take on the world (or at least your corporate inbox). He might look a little intimidating at first because he enforces the rules (rerack your weights, don‚Äôt slam, don‚Äôt do anything dangerous), but really, he‚Äôs one of the friendliest people you‚Äôll meet as long as you‚Äôre not the person trying to turn the gym into a demolition site.

And if you‚Äôre curious, check out the PT packages. They‚Äôre not just for lifting, you can use them for stretching sessions, or even kickboxing if you need to release some steam after a rough day at the office.

All in all, this gym is a gem. Show up, be respectful, rerack your weights, and don‚Äôt be that person, don‚Äôt hog machine. If everyone does their part, we‚Äôll all keep enjoying this convenient, vibrant spot in the CBD, a place where you can laugh, sweat, and recharge, together.

author: Ben Kang
text:
My home gym is Anytime Fitness Kovan (JForte). But today, I decided to venture to Anytime Fitness Upper Serangoon. Zero regrets. This gym has the legendary Hammer Strength Plate Loaded Glute Drive machine. This S Tier machine alone makes me give a 5 star rating.

Anytime Fitness Upper Serangoon > Anytime Fitness Kovan / Anytime Fitness Nex.

I‚Äôm writing this review out of my own volition: I was in the gym super early, so no chance to get the freebies.

Pros:
- Clean, well-maintained, efficient, high-quality equipment.
- Excellent music selection, not too loud. The music is on the chill end, which is perfect for the breaks between intense sets. During the sets, you can use your own earphones to play your favourite lifting songs.
- Water cooler is right next to the sink.

Possible improvements (I will transfer my membership + immediately sign my parents, relatives, friends here if they have these):
- Replace Lying Leg Curl -> Hammer Strength Select Seated Leg Curl (with thigh pads, NOT the Precor one with shin pads). Something about better stretch mediated hypertrophy. For hardcore people who still want to target the Biceps Femoris Short Head more, they can hop to the nearby iGym for their Lying Leg Curl.
- Hammer Strength Select Hip Abduction. Not a deal breaker, but great to have, cuz the nearby iGym has a Hip Abduction machine too.
- More 20kg plates on the Hammer Strength Plate Loaded Glute Drive. Cuz this is one of the few exercises which can be overloaded a lot. Having more 20kg plates here means less need to grab from the leg press and other places.
- Dedicated Bulgarian Split Squats support (short adjustable stand with the roller pad for the back leg). This won‚Äôt occupy much space.

Anyways, having the Hammer Strength Plate Loaded Glute Drive machine makes it worth the walk from Kovan MRT to Anytime Fitness Upper Serangoon, instead of the Anytime Fitness Kovan. This gym is small, but it has the Hammer Strength stuff. Hammer Strength is like the Ferrari of gym equipment.

Pro tip: the 24Hr An-Nur makmak beside it sells really clean food. Plain rice + Sambal fish + Egg. ;)

To Anytime Fitness Kovan (if you are even reading this), I am personally willing to fund these machines to make you on-par with Anytime Fitness Upper Serangoon (so I don‚Äôt need to walk that much). I‚Äôm the person who replenished the barbell hip thrust pads btw. You have so much gym real estate, so much potential, don‚Äôt waste it.

author: Kimi
text:
I visited this outlet with my son in early October for a consultation, and unfortunately, it was a very disappointing experience. There was a Malay/Indian staff member attending to us, and I was quite taken aback by how rude and dismissive he was when I asked a few basic questions about the membership options.

I was simply trying to understand the pricing and compare it to other gyms in the area, as any parent would do before making a decision. Instead of receiving helpful information, we were met with irritated looks and a tone that made it feel like we were inconveniencing him just by asking. The way he spoke to both me and my son felt unprofessional and disrespectful, as if he was doing us a favour just by having the conversation.

I rarely leave negative reviews, but this experience left a really bad impression. When you walk into a place that promotes health and wellness, you expect a certain level of respect and basic courtesy, especially when you're considering signing up. I hope the management takes this seriously and ensures their staff are better trained in customer service. No one should be made to feel small for asking questions.

If anyone is looking to sign up for a membership I seriously advice you to think twice before signing up at this outlet.
source_file: Anytime Fitness Choa Chu Kang Centre_reviews.csv

I had the joy of attending the launch of this new gym last Saturday, and I‚Äôm still buzzing from the energy. Tucked away in the basement of a rather unassuming building, this space has been completely transformed into a space that radiates warmth, grit, and genuine community spirit.

What struck me most wasn‚Äôt just the equipment or the space (though both are great), but the people. From the moment I stepped in, I was welcomed with open arms by the trainers, the members, even folks I‚Äôd never met before. It already feels like a second home for those who come here, and it‚Äôs only just opened.

Huge kudos to HM for bringing this vision to life, for creating not just a gym, but a safe, supportive, and motivating environment for people to move, sweat, and grow stronger together. So proud and excited to see where this journey leads!

The equipment is modern and comprehensive, catering to all types of workouts ‚Äî from strength training to cardio and functional exercises. Machines are always in good working condition, and any maintenance is attended to quickly.

What really sets this gym apart is the team. The staff are friendly, professional, and always ready to help. Whether it‚Äôs assisting with equipment, answering questions, or just offering a warm greeting, their positive energy makes a big difference.

It‚Äôs also a huge plus that the gym is open 24/7 ‚Äî super convenient for those with busy or irregular schedules.

If you‚Äôre looking for a supportive and clean environment to work out in Jurong, I highly recommend giving this place a try!

text:
Months back I relocated to this branch, the gym is decent and properly maintained, staffs were friendly. Most times they would offer Bread or Bananas which as really nice.

I even renewed my membership with them, but there were some admin glitches. Initially I couldn't tap in, happened for the first 2 times after renewal, possibly due to the renewal of the membership, and then I got hit with late payment fee, even though I have provided the correct card information. When I tried to clarify it on whatsapp, I felt like the staff corresponding with me on whatsapp was avoiding my questions and kept insisting that it was because it was my fault that I pay late. I tried to point out that the last 4 digits of the card that they have keyed into EzPay was wrong (it was 0000). I understand that late payment will result in late payment fee and that is understood in the contract, but this was not the case. Long story short it was acknowledged that they've processed my card details wrongly, but I had to still pay $15 for this mistake.

author: Darren Tan Wei Jie
text:
Nestled in the heart of Singapore's vibrant Buona Vista area, Anytime Fitness Buona Vista stands as a modern, well-equipped gym that delivers a high-quality workout experience around the clock. As part of the globally recognized Anytime Fitness franchise, this outlet offers 24/7 access to fitness enthusiasts of all levels, making it a top choice for professionals, students, and residents in the area.

Upon entering the gym, you're immediately greeted by a sleek, contemporary design that reflects both professionalism and comfort. The facility is exceptionally clean, spacious, and well-lit, featuring an open layout that allows for smooth navigation between different workout zones. A bright interior, complete with glass-panel walls and bold LED signage, provides an energizing atmosphere perfect for focused training.

One of the gym‚Äôs standout features is its diverse range of state-of-the-art equipment. The image shows a full set of Life Fitness machines designed for strength training, alongside free weights neatly racked against mirrored walls to allow for proper form checks. Whether you're looking to build muscle, burn fat, or tone up, there‚Äôs equipment tailored to every goal ‚Äî from seated row and chest press machines to leg curl and extension setups.

Cardio enthusiasts are equally well catered to. A row of high-end treadmills lines the side of the gym, each with built-in screens and controls for customized workouts. Their positioning along the glass windows offers a nice outside view, which enhances the experience, especially during early mornings or late-night runs. The treadmills appear new and are neatly covered, signaling proper maintenance and care for hygiene ‚Äî a hallmark of Anytime Fitness locations.

Another notable aspect is the gym‚Äôs clear attention to inclusivity and user guidance. Equipment is labeled clearly, with visual instructions and safety tips for beginners. This is especially helpful for first-time users who may need more confidence navigating gym machinery. There‚Äôs also evidence of functional training areas and possibly a space for personal training sessions or group classes ‚Äî services that Anytime Fitness often includes in its membership packages.

Conveniently located near business hubs, residential areas, and the Buona Vista MRT station, this outlet is ideal for busy professionals who need flexibility. The 24-hour access allows members to work out on their own schedule, whether early in the morning, during a lunch break, or after a long day at work. Security and access control systems ensure safety, even during off-peak hours.

In addition to its facilities, members benefit from the Anytime Fitness app, which offers workout tracking, virtual training programs, and community support. For travelers or those frequently on the move, the universal membership grants access to thousands of Anytime Fitness gyms worldwide.

In summary, Anytime Fitness Buona Vista is more than just a neighborhood gym ‚Äî it's a polished, user-friendly fitness hub that prioritizes accessibility, cleanliness, and performance. Whether you‚Äôre starting your fitness journey or a seasoned athlete, this branch offers a welcoming and fully equipped environment to help you achieve your goals, anytime.

text:
I‚Äôve been a regular member at this gym and have generally appreciated the convenient location and the friendly staff. However, I‚Äôd like to raise a concern that I hope management can address.

Several pieces of equipment, like the leg extension machine, have been out of order for over a month now, and unfortunately, there hasn‚Äôt been much visible progress in getting them repaired. Instead of acknowledging their own mistake, they shifted the blame and brushed off all accountability once I transferred clubs. Even when presented with clear proof, they showed no willingness to resolve the issue or support a long-time member. This is not about the money. It is about how a business chooses to treat its members when things go wrong. The lack of basic professionalism, follow-through, and courtesy has been incredibly disappointing.
I would not recommend this location to anyone who values proper service and accountability.

author: Chi Hong Hwang
text:
I have been training under Kirtan for about 2 to 3 years. He is great. He has deep knowledge about functional training and helped me through chronic pain in both my shoulders. He still continues to go for more training and certification and works the new knowledge into my weekly training. Now that we've moved to this gym, I'm pleased that he has incorporated heavier weights into my workout. I always enjoy my sessions with Kirtan. He's easy going and easy to talk to. Over the years we've become friends.

They gym is newly renovated so it is clean, well lit and well equipped. There's a good buzz. I was surprised at the many bodybuilder enthusiasts there on a weekday evening but still there was little wait for machines. The gym was located in the basement. A door in the car park opens to the gym entrance after a shot passage. So park at the correct side of the car park.

The mall itself is undergoing a revitalisation. Parts of it  was still somewhat worn and old but then it makes you appreciate all the more how bright, new and shiny the gym is.

author: Durrah Rafi
text:
Very disappointed with Anytime Fitness Paya Lebar. A payment failed due to a bank issue beyond my control, yet I was still charged a late fee. When I reached out for help, the gym dismissed my concerns and pushed all responsibility onto me. Their response showed no empathy or willingness to support a paying customer.

If you value fair treatment, I would not recommend this branch. Other Anytime Fitness locations provide better management and customer service, save yourself the frustration.

This was the response I got from them when I asked for help:
‚ÄúGood morning, if the issue is due to bank , then bank should bear this extra cost incurred to you and do the needful from their end. Hope you understand our side that just like you, we, AFPL can not bear this extra cost either as its not even our fault.‚Äù

As a paying customer, I had expected more understanding and support from the gym. Definitely not continuing my membership here after this experience.

author: Keerthana Ravichandran
text:
BoxCore Fitness class was the best! all thanks to our incredible Trainer Kirtan! From the very beginning, the energy was high and the atmosphere was welcoming.

We kicked things off with a fun and energising warm-up that really set the tone. Kirtan expertly taught us key boxing techniques like the forward punch, slip, uppercut, and hook. Each move was broken down with clear explanations, and Kirtan patiently guided us through every step, making sure we got the form and rhythm right.

What truly stood out was how well-versed and passionate Kirtan is in boxing, his experience shines through in every instruction and correction. Whether you're brand new or just brushing up your skills, you'll learn so much!

We wrapped up with a cool down and stretching session that was not only effective but also really enjoyable, a perfect way to end an intense workout. Overall, it was an fun experience.

outlet: Anytime Fitness Ang Mo Kio South
author: Pushpendra Thakur
text:
Dear Team,

I‚Äôve been noticing a growing issue that‚Äôs affecting many serious members‚Äô workout experience:
A number of younger gym-goers often occupy machines for long periods, doing only one rep, then resting for 2‚Äì3 minutes, adding more weight, and repeating the same with minimal actual training volume.

This behavior not only limits access for others but also disrupts the flow during busy hours. Many of these users seem more focused on ego lifting or social media clips than productive workouts.

Suggestions:
‚Ä¢ Kindly have trainers monitor equipment usage during peak times
‚Ä¢ Display reminders on proper gym etiquette (e.g., time limits per machine during rush hours)
‚Ä¢ Educate new lifters on structured workout sets, reps, and rest intervals

We all start somewhere ‚Äî but the gym should also be a space of mutual respect and serious training. I hope management can take steps to maintain a more focused and respectful gym environment.

Thanks for your attention.

‚Äî A regular, respectful member
